RACHEL, DON'T LET GO OF ME.
JUST HOLD ON.

96
00:03:56,402 --> 00:03:59,538
DON'T LET GO.
I'M AFRAID. DON'T LET GO.

97
00:03:59,539 --> 00:04:02,658
I'VE GOT YOU.
I'VE GOT YOU.

98
00:04:06,412 --> 00:04:07,045
HELP!

99
00:04:09,549 --> 00:04:11,417
[RADIO PLAYS LOUDLY]

100
00:04:11,417 --> 00:04:12,668
HELP US!

101
00:04:13,920 --> 00:04:15,171
OVER HERE.
WE NEED HELP!

102
00:04:15,171 --> 00:04:16,422
PLEASE, HELP ME.

103
00:04:17,674 --> 00:04:20,176
NO! AAH!

104
00:04:20,176 --> 00:04:21,427
NO! NO!

105
00:04:23,313 --> 00:04:23,930
HOLD ON!

106
00:04:23,930 --> 00:04:27,066
RACHEL!
AAH! CARLA!

107
00:04:27,066 --> 00:04:28,317
HELP!

108
00:04:28,318 --> 00:04:29,569
HELP!

109
00:04:29,569 --> 00:04:32,071
OH, MY GOD!
PLEASE DON'T LET GO!

110
00:04:32,071 --> 00:04:33,939
RACHEL! HOLD ON!

111
00:04:33,940 --> 00:04:36,442
PLEASE DON'T LET ME FALL.

112
00:04:36,442 --> 00:04:37,693
DON'T LET GO!

113
00:04:37,694 --> 00:04:40,196
JUST HOLD ON.

114
00:04:41,447 --> 00:04:42,080
DON'T LET GO.

115
00:04:45,201 --> 00:04:46,452
Mark: DON'T LET GO!

116
00:04:50,840 --> 00:04:52,091
OH, MY GOD!

117
00:04:52,091 --> 00:04:54,593
AAH!

118
00:04:55,845 --> 00:04:57,713
RACHEL!

119
00:05:34,967 --> 00:05:38,086
Man: CARLA AND RACHEL WERE
CLOSER THAN MOST SISTERS.

120
00:05:38,721 --> 00:05:41,840
CARLA WAS HER GUARDIAN,
HER CARETAKER.

121
00:05:41,841 --> 00:05:43,726
RACHEL, CARLA'S BEST FRIEND

122
00:05:44,344 --> 00:05:46,846
AND SPICE TO HER LIFE.

123
00:05:46,846 --> 00:05:49,348
TWO YEARS AGO,
WHEN WE GATHERED HERE,

124
00:05:49,349 --> 00:05:51,851
WE BADE FAREWELL
TO THE PARENTS

125
00:05:51,851 --> 00:05:53,102
OF RACHEL AND CARLA.

126
00:05:53,736 --> 00:05:56,238
TODAY, TRAGICALLY, WE COME
TO BID FAREWELL TO RACHEL.

127
00:05:56,239 --> 00:05:58,107
IN A MOMENT,

128
00:05:58,107 --> 00:06:01,860
HER MORTAL DUST WILL
JOIN THAT OF HER PARENTS ON THE LAKE,

129
00:06:01,861 --> 00:06:06,248
EVEN AS HER SOUL JOINS
THEIR SOULS IN HEAVEN.

130
00:06:06,249 --> 00:06:11,871
CARLA HAS ASKED ME TO READ
<i>NOTHING GOLD CAN STAY</i> <i>BY ROBERT FROST</i>

131
00:06:11,871 --> 00:06:15,624
AS SHE SCATTERS THE ASHES
ON THE LAKE.

132
00:06:20,012 --> 00:06:24,383
"NATURE'S FIRST GREEN
IS GOLD,

133
00:06:24,384 --> 00:06:27,520
HER HARDEST HUE TO HOLD."

134
00:06:28,771 --> 00:06:31,273
"HER EARLY LEAF'S A FLOWER,

135
00:06:31,274 --> 00:06:35,027
BUT ONLY FOR AN HOUR."

136
00:06:35,027 --> 00:06:36,278
Girl: CARLA!

137
00:06:36,279 --> 00:06:40,650
"THEN LEAF
SUBSIDES TO LEAF."

138
00:06:40,650 --> 00:06:43,152
Girl:
I'M AFRAID, CARLA!

139
00:06:43,152 --> 00:06:46,288
"SO HEAT SANK TO GRIEF."

140
00:06:46,289 --> 00:06:48,157
Girl: CARLA!

141
00:06:49,409 --> 00:06:53,162
"SO DAWN GOES DOWN TO DAY."

142
00:06:54,414 --> 00:06:56,299
Girl: CARLA!

143
00:06:56,299 --> 00:06:58,801
I'M AFRAID,
CARLA!

144
00:06:58,801 --> 00:07:01,303
COME ON. JUST TIP IT
AND LET HER GO FREE.

145
00:07:01,304 --> 00:07:01,921
JUST LET HER GO.

146
00:07:02,555 --> 00:07:05,674
"NOTHING GOLD CAN STAY."

147
00:07:09,595 --> 00:07:10,228
AAH!

148
00:07:12,732 --> 00:07:13,349
RACHEL.

149
00:07:13,349 --> 00:07:15,851
[MURMURING]

150
00:07:15,852 --> 00:07:17,103
RACHEL?

151
00:07:19,605 --> 00:07:21,490
SHE WANTED
TO PULL ME IN.

152
00:07:21,491 --> 00:07:23,359
HEY, HEY. SHH! SHH!

153
00:07:23,359 --> 00:07:23,992
I COULDN'T BREATHE.

154
00:07:24,610 --> 00:07:25,243
SHH! SHH! SHH!

155
00:07:25,244 --> 00:07:26,495
SHE HAD HER HAND COME OUT--

156
00:07:26,496 --> 00:07:28,364
Mark: IT'S OK.

157
00:07:28,364 --> 00:07:30,249
[CROWD MURMURS]

158
00:07:34,620 --> 00:07:36,505
I WANT TO GO HOME.

159
00:07:37,757 --> 00:07:38,374
CARLA, WHAT AB--

160
00:07:39,008 --> 00:07:40,259
NO. I WANT TO GO HOME NOW!

161
00:08:02,148 --> 00:08:03,399
THE ROSES ARE BEAUTIFUL.

162
00:08:04,033 --> 00:08:06,351
THEY ALWAYS WERE
HER FAVORITE FLOWER.

163
00:08:06,352 --> 00:08:10,406
MAYBE IT'S BETTER
SHE STAYS WITH US A WHILE LONGER.

164
00:08:10,406 --> 00:08:11,657
YOU THINK?

165
00:08:22,301 --> 00:08:23,552
CAN I SEE?

166
00:08:27,924 --> 00:08:29,809
WE ALWAYS WERE TOGETHER.

167
00:08:30,977 --> 00:08:33,479
AND THE WAY SHE BELIEVED
IN LIFE AFTER DEATH AND KARMA,

168
00:08:34,096 --> 00:08:37,232
IT'S PROBABLY BEST
SHE'S HERE.

169
00:08:37,233 --> 00:08:41,487
AFTER ALL, MOM AND DAD
DID LEAVE THE PLACE TO BOTH OF US.

170
00:08:41,487 --> 00:08:43,355
CARLA...

171
00:08:44,607 --> 00:08:46,442
LOOK AT ME.

172
00:08:48,327 --> 00:08:50,162
LOOK AT ME.

173
00:08:51,414 --> 00:08:55,167
WHAT HAPPENED AT
THE LAKE WAS NOT RACHEL.

174
00:08:55,167 --> 00:08:57,035
SHE'S GONE.

175
00:08:57,036 --> 00:09:00,789
IF SHE'S GONE,
IT'S BECAUSE I LET HER GO.

176
00:09:00,790 --> 00:09:02,675
DON'T DO THIS
TO YOURSELF.

177
00:09:02,675 --> 00:09:04,543
I WAS RESPONSIBLE FOR HER.

178
00:09:04,544 --> 00:09:07,680
RACHEL DEPENDED ON ME
FOR EVERYTHING.

179
00:09:09,549 --> 00:09:11,968
SHE WAS LOOKING
INTO MY EYES,

180
00:09:11,968 --> 00:09:14,470
AND I COULDN'T HOLD ON.

181
00:09:14,470 --> 00:09:15,721
I CAN SEE HER FACE,

182
00:09:15,721 --> 00:09:19,474
THAT LOOK OF HORROR
AND BETRAYAL.

183
00:09:19,475 --> 00:09:21,360
I CAN SEE IT NOW.

184
00:09:21,360 --> 00:09:23,862
I CAN SEE IT
WHEN I SLEEP--

185
00:09:23,863 --> 00:09:25,114
THAT'S NOT REAL.

186
00:09:26,365 --> 00:09:28,867
IT'S NOT RACHEL.

187
00:09:28,868 --> 00:09:30,119
YOU KNOW THAT.

188
00:09:49,472 --> 00:09:51,340
Girl: I'M AFRAID.

189
00:09:52,592 --> 00:09:55,728
CAN'T YOU COME UP
AND GET IT, CARLA?

190
00:09:55,728 --> 00:09:57,563
YOU'RE SO MUCH BIGGER.

191
00:09:57,563 --> 00:09:59,231
JUST REACH, YOU SISSY.

192
00:09:59,231 --> 00:10:00,482
DO AS I TELL YOU.

193
00:10:00,483 --> 00:10:02,351
CAN'T YOU COME UP
AND GET IT, CARLA?

194
00:10:02,351 --> 00:10:04,236
YOU'RE SO MUCH BIGGER.

195
00:10:04,236 --> 00:10:06,104
I'M AFRAID.

196
00:10:06,105 --> 00:10:07,356
COME DOWN.

197
00:10:07,356 --> 00:10:09,241
DOWN WHEREVER
YOU ARE.

198
00:10:09,241 --> 00:10:11,109
DOWN, DOWN,
WHEREVER YOU ARE.

199
00:10:11,110 --> 00:10:12,995
DOWN, DOWN,
WHEREVER YOU ARE.

200
00:10:12,995 --> 00:10:14,246
COME UP, PLEASE.

201
00:10:14,246 --> 00:10:16,748
RACHEL!
AAH!

202
00:10:46,896 --> 00:10:48,781
[DOOR OPENS]

203
00:10:50,032 --> 00:10:51,283
GOOD MORNING.

204
00:10:51,283 --> 00:10:54,402
HI. DIDN'T SLEEP WELL
LAST NIGHT, DID YOU?

205
00:10:54,403 --> 00:10:56,905
UH, NO.
I HAD A BAD DREAM.

206
00:10:56,906 --> 00:11:00,042
YEAH? WHAT ABOUT?

207
00:11:00,042 --> 00:11:01,910
WHEN RACHEL
AND I WERE KIDS,

208
00:11:01,911 --> 00:11:03,796
THERE WAS A KITE
STUCK IN A GUTTER.

209
00:11:03,796 --> 00:11:05,664
I CONNED HER
INTO GOING UP TO GET IT,

210
00:11:05,665 --> 00:11:07,550
AND I NEARLY GOT HER KILLED.

211
00:11:07,550 --> 00:11:10,052
SHE FELL
FROM THE ATTIC WINDOW.

212
00:11:10,052 --> 00:11:11,920
DID THAT REALLY HAPPEN?

213
00:11:11,921 --> 00:11:16,175
YEAH. IF IT HADN'T HAVE
BEEN FOR THE HEDGE, SHE WOULD'VE DIED.

214
00:11:16,175 --> 00:11:18,677
I SPENT THE REST OF MY LIFE
TRYING TO REGAIN HER TRUST.

215
00:11:19,311 --> 00:11:21,179
YOU NEVER
TOLD ME THAT BEFORE.

216
00:11:21,180 --> 00:11:24,316
ARE THESE THE PICTURES
FROM THE MOUNTAINS?

217
00:11:24,316 --> 00:11:26,818
NO, I THREW THOSE AWAY.

218
00:11:26,819 --> 00:11:28,687
WELL, YOU DIDN'T
HAVE TO DO THAT.

219
00:11:28,688 --> 00:11:29,939
I COULD'VE HANDLED IT.

220
00:11:30,573 --> 00:11:32,441
I KNOW. I JUST THINK
IT'S BETTER WE MOVE ON.

221
00:11:32,441 --> 00:11:33,692
I'LL TAKE SOME NEW ONES.

222
00:11:33,693 --> 00:11:35,578
I DON'T NEED NEW ONES.

223
00:11:36,195 --> 00:11:38,080
I THINK
YOU'LL FEEL BETTER WITH NEW ONES.

224
00:11:38,080 --> 00:11:39,948
I ALSO THINK

225
00:11:39,949 --> 00:11:42,451
MAYBE WE SHOULD FIND
A DOCTOR FOR YOU TO SEE.

226
00:11:42,451 --> 00:11:44,336
I'LL BE FINE, ALL RIGHT?

227
00:11:44,336 --> 00:11:46,204
ALL I NEED
IS A GOOD NIGHT'S SLEEP.

228
00:11:46,205 --> 00:11:48,090
OTHERWISE, I'M HUNKY-DORY.

229
00:11:49,959 --> 00:11:53,095
OK, THEN, HOW ABOUT
NOT GOING TO WORK TODAY?

230
00:11:53,095 --> 00:11:56,848
GOING TO WORK
IS THE BEST THING THAT I COULD DO.

231
00:11:56,849 --> 00:12:01,220
BESIDES, I'VE GOT
AN EXCLUSIVE WITH SENATOR BILLINGS.

232
00:12:01,220 --> 00:12:01,853
HE'S RESIGNING,

233
00:12:02,471 --> 00:12:04,973
AND I'M NOT GOING
TO LET HARRIS GET THE STORY.

234
00:12:07,476 --> 00:12:08,727
I'M OK.

235
00:12:08,728 --> 00:12:09,979
ALL RIGHT.

236
00:12:09,979 --> 00:12:11,864
I'LL BE
AT THE STUDIO.

237
00:12:12,481 --> 00:12:13,732
OK.

238
00:12:16,235 --> 00:12:17,486
WAIT UP.

239
00:12:26,245 --> 00:12:27,496
HE'S IN 3415, RIGHT?

240
00:12:27,496 --> 00:12:30,632
YEAH. PENTHOUSE.
OUR TAX DOLLARS AT WORK.

241
00:12:35,638 --> 00:12:36,255
[DING]

242
00:12:38,140 --> 00:12:40,642
Woman: I'LL MEET YOU
IN THE CONFERENCE IN DETROIT.

243
00:12:41,260 --> 00:12:43,762
Man: DID YOU
NOTICE IF THEY HAD A LAUNDRY SERVICE?

244
00:12:43,763 --> 00:12:45,014
Woman: SEE YOU LATER.

245
00:12:45,014 --> 00:12:46,265
Man: YEAH, THEY'VE GOT
A LAUNDRY.

246
00:12:46,265 --> 00:12:47,516
THEY'LL DO IT FOR YOU,
ACTUALLY.

