WE WORK AS A GROUP.

475
00:28:26,905 --> 00:28:28,773
SO I'M FLYING
FOR THE AIRLINES

476
00:28:28,773 --> 00:28:32,526
AND--AND 15 YEARS WITHOUT
AN INCIDENT, BUT...

477
00:28:32,527 --> 00:28:35,663
ONE DAY WE'RE ON--
WE'RE ON APPROACH TO PITTSBURGH,

478
00:28:35,663 --> 00:28:37,531
DESCENDING TO 27,000 FEET,

479
00:28:37,532 --> 00:28:40,668
WHEN, LIKE, THIS...THIS DOOR
OPENS UP IN MY MIND

480
00:28:40,668 --> 00:28:41,919
THAT I DIDN'T EVEN KNOW
WAS THERE

481
00:28:42,537 --> 00:28:45,673
AND OUT--OUT STEPS
THIS--THIS URGE TO J-JUMP OUT OF THE PLANE.

482
00:28:45,673 --> 00:28:46,924
I WAS PARALYZED--

483
00:28:46,925 --> 00:28:48,176
THE COPILOT HAD
TO LAND THE PLANE.

484
00:28:48,176 --> 00:28:49,427
OLD BENNY HERE,
HE COULDN'T MOVE.

485
00:28:49,427 --> 00:28:51,929
DO YOU MIND IF I TELL
MY OWN STORY, ZAK? DO YA, HUH?

486
00:28:51,930 --> 00:28:54,432
THE DOC--THE DOC'S
HELPED ME TRACE IT BACK

487
00:28:54,432 --> 00:28:56,300
TO WHEN I WAS IN THE ARMY.

488
00:28:56,301 --> 00:28:59,437
I WAS A FIRST INFANTRY
PARATROOPER--THE SCREAMING EAGLES, YOU KNOW?

489
00:28:59,437 --> 00:29:01,305
UP IN THE PLANE WITH MY
JUMP BUDDY, IVAN IRELAND--

490
00:29:01,306 --> 00:29:02,557
DO YOU BELIEVE THAT NAME?

491
00:29:02,557 --> 00:29:04,442
WHO NAMES THEIR KID
IVAN IRE--

492
00:29:04,442 --> 00:29:05,693
IT WAS A FREEFALL EXERCISE.

493
00:29:05,693 --> 00:29:07,561
IVAN JUMPED FIRST,
BUT HIS CHUTE DIDN'T OPEN,

494
00:29:07,562 --> 00:29:10,698
AND I DOVE OUT, AND I
TRIED TO CATCH UP TO HIM, BUT I WAS TOO LATE.

495
00:29:10,698 --> 00:29:12,566
IF I HADN'T PULLED MY OWN
RIP CORD, I WOULD'VE GONE IN WITH HIM.

496
00:29:12,567 --> 00:29:15,703
I WATCHED HIM FALL.
I SAW HIM HIT THE GROUND.

497
00:29:15,703 --> 00:29:17,571
YEAH, BUT YOU DID
THE BEST YOU COULD.

498
00:29:17,572 --> 00:29:20,074
I SHOULD HAVE GONE IN
WITH HIM.

499
00:29:20,074 --> 00:29:23,210
THE FACT IS, HE...

500
00:29:23,211 --> 00:29:25,713
HE WASN'T FEELING RIGHT
THAT DAY.

501
00:29:25,713 --> 00:29:28,832
HE DIDN'T EVEN TRUST HIMSELF
TO PACK HIS OWN CHUTE.

502
00:29:28,833 --> 00:29:31,335
I DID IT.

503
00:29:32,587 --> 00:29:34,472
OOPS.

504
00:29:34,472 --> 00:29:36,974
LISTEN, YOU STUPID
LITTLE PUNK!

505
00:29:36,975 --> 00:29:39,477
OKAY!
WE HAVIN' FUN YET?

506
00:29:39,477 --> 00:29:42,596
COME ON, BENNY.
READY TO HIT THE TRAIL?

507
00:29:42,597 --> 00:29:43,230
LET'S GO.

508
00:29:46,985 --> 00:29:48,236
OH, OH, ZAK!

509
00:29:49,487 --> 00:29:50,104
GET A LIFE!

510
00:29:50,104 --> 00:29:51,355
Sadowski: YOU OK, BENNY?
YOU ALL RIGHT?

511
00:29:51,356 --> 00:29:52,607
I'M OK, YEAH.

512
00:29:54,492 --> 00:29:55,743
YEAH.

513
00:29:56,995 --> 00:30:00,114
WHOO!

514
00:30:00,114 --> 00:30:02,449
WHOA! COME ON, BEN!

515
00:30:02,450 --> 00:30:04,952
WHOO-HOO! BENNY,
COME ON OUT HERE!

516
00:30:05,587 --> 00:30:07,455
HE'S GONNA FALL.

517
00:30:07,455 --> 00:30:09,340
OH, YEAH.
WE SHOULD BE SO LUCKY.

518
00:30:09,340 --> 00:30:11,842
NO, UNFORTUNATELY,
HE'S JUST SHOWING OFF.

519
00:30:11,843 --> 00:30:13,094
Hallie: HE USED TO BE
LIKE THE REST OF US,

520
00:30:13,094 --> 00:30:14,345
THEN HE GOT CURED
TOO WELL.

521
00:30:14,345 --> 00:30:15,596
NOW HE'S COUNTER-PHOBIC.

522
00:30:16,214 --> 00:30:18,716
OBSESSED WITH PROVING
HE'S NOT AFRAID OF HEIGHTS.

523
00:30:18,716 --> 00:30:20,601
Sadowski: HEY, ZAK!

524
00:30:20,602 --> 00:30:22,470
KNOCK IT OFF,
WILL YOU?

525
00:30:23,104 --> 00:30:24,355
SHOW SOME RESPECT
FOR OTHERS.

526
00:30:24,355 --> 00:30:25,606
COME ON, BEN!

527
00:30:25,607 --> 00:30:28,109
HE EVEN GOT A JOB
WASHING WINDOWS ON CLARKE TOWER,

528
00:30:28,109 --> 00:30:29,360
JUST SO HE CAN LOOK
DOWN.

529
00:30:29,978 --> 00:30:32,480
OH, BEN, MAN,
IT'S GREAT!

530
00:30:32,480 --> 00:30:35,616
I'M HOPING HE DIES
FROM THE CURE.

531
00:30:35,617 --> 00:30:37,485
BOO!

532
00:30:37,485 --> 00:30:39,987
OK, BEN, YOU'RE NEXT.
NO WISECRACKS.

533
00:30:39,988 --> 00:30:41,239
WE SUPPORT EACH OTHER.

534
00:30:41,239 --> 00:30:43,741
Zak: PIECE O'CAKE, BUDDY.
COME ON.

535
00:30:43,741 --> 00:30:44,992
COME ON, MAN,
YOU CAN DO IT.

536
00:30:44,993 --> 00:30:48,129
I'M SUPPORTING.
THAT'S SUPPORT, ISN'T IT?

537
00:30:48,129 --> 00:30:49,380
Sadowski: OK, BEN.
COME ON.

538
00:30:49,380 --> 00:30:53,133
FOLLOW MY VOICE.

539
00:30:53,134 --> 00:30:55,636
COME ON. ONE STEP...

540
00:30:55,637 --> 00:30:57,505
THEN ANOTHER.

541
00:30:57,505 --> 00:31:00,007
FOLLOW MY VOICE.

542
00:31:00,008 --> 00:31:03,144
KEEPING MOVING.
DON'T STOP. KEEP MOVING.

543
00:31:03,144 --> 00:31:05,012
THAT'S IT.
YOU'RE DOING GREAT.

544
00:31:05,013 --> 00:31:08,149
YOU'RE DOING GREAT.
THAT'S RIGHT.

545
00:31:08,149 --> 00:31:08,766
COME ON, BEN.

546
00:31:08,766 --> 00:31:10,017
WHY THE BLINDFOLD?

547
00:31:10,018 --> 00:31:13,154
SO HE CAN CONCENTRATE
ON DOC'S VOICE.

548
00:31:13,154 --> 00:31:16,273
Sadowski:
YOU'RE DOING GREAT. YOU'RE DOING GREAT!

549
00:31:16,274 --> 00:31:18,776
I DON'T THINK I CAN DO THAT.

550
00:31:18,776 --> 00:31:20,027
Sadowski: FOLLOW IT.

551
00:31:20,028 --> 00:31:22,530
YOU DON'T HAVE TO GO
TOO FAR ON YOUR FIRST TIME OUT.

552
00:31:22,530 --> 00:31:23,781
BUT HE'LL PUSH YOU.

553
00:31:23,781 --> 00:31:26,283
IF YOU DON'T DO
WHAT HE SAYS, HE'LL COUNT TO 3...

554
00:31:26,918 --> 00:31:28,786
AND THEN IT'S OVER.
YOU'RE OUT OF THE GROUP.

555
00:31:29,420 --> 00:31:31,288
FOLLOW MY VOICE.
COME ON, BEN!

556
00:31:31,289 --> 00:31:33,174
[WHINES]

557
00:31:33,174 --> 00:31:36,927
STAND UP! NO, NO, NO!
STAND UP! STAND UP!

558
00:31:36,928 --> 00:31:41,299
THAT'S IT. COME ON,
KEEP COMING. KEEP COMING.

559
00:31:41,299 --> 00:31:43,184
FARTHER THAN LAST TIME.

560
00:31:43,184 --> 00:31:45,052
FARTHER THAN LAST TIME.

561
00:31:45,053 --> 00:31:46,304
THAT'S IT. STOP!

562
00:31:46,304 --> 00:31:48,172
[WHINES]

563
00:31:51,893 --> 00:31:53,778
LOOK AROUND.

564
00:31:55,647 --> 00:31:57,532
NOT BAD.

565
00:31:57,532 --> 00:31:59,400
MUCH BETTER
THAN LAST TIME.

566
00:32:00,034 --> 00:32:01,902
THAT'S A LOT FARTHER
THAN THE LAST TIME.

567
00:32:02,537 --> 00:32:04,405
Hallie: YOU'RE
DOIN' IT, BEN!

568
00:32:04,405 --> 00:32:05,656
WE LOVE YOU, BEN.

569
00:32:05,657 --> 00:32:06,908
NOT!

570
00:32:08,793 --> 00:32:10,661
CARLA, HAVE YOU
SEEN THE DROP?

571
00:32:10,662 --> 00:32:12,547
IT'S 300 FEET,
STRAIGHT DOWN.

572
00:32:12,547 --> 00:32:13,798
PLEASE DON'T.

573
00:32:13,798 --> 00:32:15,666
[IMITATES
FALLING OBJECT]

574
00:32:15,667 --> 00:32:16,918
KNOCK IT OFF, ZAK!

575
00:32:16,918 --> 00:32:18,169
JAGGED ROCKS,
WATER BOILING UP--

576
00:32:18,803 --> 00:32:19,420
STOP IT!

577
00:32:21,923 --> 00:32:23,808
CLOSE YOUR EYES.

578
00:32:25,677 --> 00:32:27,562
UM...

579
00:32:27,562 --> 00:32:28,179
I'M SORRY.

580
00:32:28,179 --> 00:32:31,315
Sadowski:
DON'T SAY "I'M SORRY."

581
00:32:31,316 --> 00:32:32,567
SAY "I'M SCARED."

582
00:32:33,184 --> 00:32:33,817
I'M SCARED.

583
00:32:33,818 --> 00:32:35,686
WELL, THAT'S NOTHING
TO APOLOGIZE FOR.

584
00:32:35,687 --> 00:32:37,572
NOTHING TO BE ASHAMED OF.

585
00:32:41,326 --> 00:32:43,194
I CAN'T.

586
00:32:43,194 --> 00:32:44,445
[CLUCKS]

587
00:32:44,445 --> 00:32:45,696
UNH.
[COUGHS]

588
00:32:45,697 --> 00:32:48,833
BUT YOU HAVE TO DO IT.
YOU'RE COMMITTED TO DO IT.

589
00:32:48,833 --> 00:32:50,084
WELL, I CAN'T.

590
00:32:52,587 --> 00:32:53,838
ONE...

591
00:32:56,341 --> 00:32:57,592
COME ON, CARLA.

592
00:32:57,592 --> 00:32:59,460
JUST CLOSE
YOUR EYES, CARLA.

593
00:33:00,094 --> 00:33:00,711
2...

594
00:33:03,214 --> 00:33:05,099
MMM.

595
00:33:08,853 --> 00:33:12,606
OK. OK.

596
00:33:22,617 --> 00:33:23,868
COME ON.

597
00:33:26,988 --> 00:33:28,873
STEP.

598
00:33:38,249 --> 00:33:40,134
UHH...

599
00:33:58,903 --> 00:34:02,022
THAT'S ALL I WANT YOU
TO DO TODAY. JUST TRUST ME.

600
00:34:03,908 --> 00:34:07,661
MMM...

601
00:34:07,662 --> 00:34:10,164
YOU KNOW WHY I LET ZAK
SHOW OFF THE WAY HE DOES?

602
00:34:10,164 --> 00:34:12,032
NO, I GUESS NOT.

603
00:34:12,033 --> 00:34:15,169
BECAUSE HIS COURAGE
IS CONTAGIOUS.

604
00:34:15,787 --> 00:34:17,038
SO IS YOUR FEAR.

605
00:34:17,038 --> 00:34:19,540
FEAR CAN'T HURT YOU
UNLESS YOU SURRENDER TO IT,

606
00:34:20,174 --> 00:34:21,425
BUT ONCE YOU DO,

607
00:34:21,426 --> 00:34:22,677
IT CAN KILL YOU.

608
00:34:25,797 --> 00:34:27,048
JOCELYN, YOU'RE NEXT.

609
00:34:33,304 --> 00:34:35,806
[MARK LAUGHS]

610
00:34:35,807 --> 00:34:38,309
OK, GIVE ME SOME...
RIGHT HERE.

611
00:34:38,309 --> 00:34:40,728
WELL, YOU LOOK BETTER
THAN I'VE SEEN YOU LOOK IN WEEKS.

612
00:34:40,728 --> 00:34:43,197
IT'S THE BEST I'VE FELT.

613
00:34:43,197 --> 00:34:46,200
I'M WITH PEOPLE WHO
UNDERSTAND ME.

614
00:34:46,200 --> 00:34:48,702
IT'S AMAZING HOW FAST PEOPLE
CAN BOND WHEN THEY HAVE A COMMON ENEMY.

615
00:34:48,703 --> 00:34:50,488
I'M THINKING I MIGHT BE ABLE
TO GO BACK TO WORK.

616
00:34:50,488 --> 00:34:52,990
YEAH.

617
00:34:53,624 --> 00:34:56,627
I THINK YOU'RE PROBABLY
THE HEALTHIEST ONE OF THE BUNCH, AREN'T YOU?

618
00:34:56,627 --> 00:34:58,462
HAS HE ACTUALLY EVER
CURED ANYONE, THIS DOCTOR?

619
00:34:59,080 --> 00:34:59,713
YES!

620
00:34:59,714 --> 00:35:01,582
ACTUALLY,
THIS KID ZAK.

621
00:35:01,582 --> 00:35:04,668
HE'S, UH, WELL, ACTUALLY,
NOW, HE'S A COUNTER-PHOBIC.

622
00:35:05,303 --> 00:35:05,920
COUNTER-PHOBIC?

623
00:35:05,920 --> 00:35:07,171
YEAH, DON'T YOU--

624
00:35:07,171 --> 00:35:09,056
HE'S, UH...
AFRAID OF COUNTERS.

625
00:35:09,056 --> 00:35:10,307
YEAH, RIGHT.

626
00:35:10,308 --> 00:35:10,925
HE FREAKS OUT
IN DINERS.

627
00:35:10,925 --> 00:35:12,810
EXACTLY.

628
00:35:12,810 --> 00:35:14,645
NO, HE HAS TO PROVE
HE'S NOT A PHOBIC.

629
00:35:14,645 --> 00:35:17,147
HE WASHES WINDOWS
AT CLARKE TOWER JUST TO KNOW HE'S OK.

630
00:35:17,148 --> 00:35:19,016
OH, YEAH, HE'S HEALTHY.

631
00:35:19,016 --> 00:35:22,753
THE DOCTOR'S WORKING ON
A SPECIAL PROGRAM FOR HIM, BRING HIM BACK TO NORMAL.

632
00:35:22,753 --> 00:35:24,521
WHATEVER THAT IS.

633
00:35:33,164 --> 00:35:35,666
HEY, MR. PETERSON.
IT'S ZAK.

634
00:35:35,666 --> 00:35:36,283
Peterson: YEAH.

635
00:35:36,918 --> 00:35:38,786
UH, BOB NEVER
SHOWED TODAY.

636
00:35:38,786 --> 00:35:43,173
YEAH,
AND THERE'S NO ANSWER AT HIS HOUSE EITHER.

637
00:35:43,174 --> 00:35:46,927
YEAH, I GUESS
I CAN DO THE WORK.

638
00:35:46,928 --> 00:35:49,430
IS HE GOING TO SHOW UP,
THOUGH?

639
00:35:51,933 --> 00:35:53,184
YEAH, HEY, NO PROBLEM.

640
00:35:53,184 --> 00:35:55,686
I MEAN, I DO MOST
OF THE WORK ANYWAY, RIGHT?

641
00:35:55,686 --> 00:35:57,554
SO DOES THIS MEAN
YOU'RE, UH, GOING TO PAY ME DOUBLE TODAY?

642
00:35:58,189 --> 00:35:58,806
[CLICK AND DIAL TONE]

643
00:35:58,806 --> 00:36:01,308
WHAT? HELLO?

644
00:36:01,309 --> 00:36:01,942
[BEEP]

645
00:36:01,943 --> 00:36:03,194
THERE'S NO NEED
TO BE RUDE.

646
00:36:23,214 --> 00:36:26,967
FEEL THE RUSH!
WHOO!

647
00:36:35,726 --> 00:36:40,731
[FOOTSTEPS]

648
00:36:45,102 --> 00:36:46,987
BOB?

649
00:37:05,756 --> 00:37:08,258
[GRAVEL CRUNCHES]

650
00:37:10,761 --> 00:37:12,629
[SCREAMING]

651
00:37:18,035 --> 00:37:21,171
Female Reporter:
THE 19-YEAR-OLD UNIVERSITY STUDENT, ZACHARY CARTER,

652
00:37:21,172 --> 00:37:23,040
FELL TO HIS DEATH
JUST BEFORE DAWN TODAY

653
00:37:23,040 --> 00:37:26,176
FROM THE WINDOW CLEANING
SCAFFOLD HE WAS WORKING ON.

654
00:37:26,177 --> 00:37:31,182
THE SCAFFOLD ITSELF
WAS INSPECTED AND FOUND TO BE IN WORKING ORDER.

655
00:37:31,182 --> 00:37:34,301
POLICE SAY THE YOUTH WAS
WORKING ALONE, HOWEVER,

656
00:37:34,302 --> 00:37:37,438
WHICH IS AGAINST
OSHA SAFETY RULES.

657
00:37:37,438 --> 00:37:41,191
[EXCITED CONVERSATION]

658
00:37:41,192 --> 00:37:42,443
HI, GUYS.

659
00:37:42,443 --> 00:37:43,060
HI.
HI.

660
00:37:43,694 --> 00:37:44,311
WHERE'S SADOWSKI?

661
00:37:44,312 --> 00:37:45,563
HE'S IN HIS OFFICE
WITH THE POLICE.

662
00:37:45,563 --> 00:37:47,448
WHAT ARE THE POLICE
DOING HERE?

663
00:37:47,448 --> 00:37:48,065
THEY THINK HE'S
INVOLVED SOMEHOW.

664
00:37:48,065 --> 00:37:50,567
ZAK WAS BLINDFOLDED.
DID YOU KNOW THAT?

665
00:37:50,568 --> 00:37:51,819
NO.

666
00:37:51,819 --> 00:37:54,321
WE'RE THE ONLY ONES
WHO KNOW THAT DOC USES A BLINDFOLD.

667
00:37:54,322 --> 00:37:55,573
WE KNOW IT
WAS NONE OF US,

668
00:37:55,573 --> 00:37:57,458
BECAUSE NONE OF US
COULD GET UP ON THAT ROOF ALONE.

669
00:37:57,458 --> 00:37:59,326
UNLESS SOMEBODY'S
FAKING IT.

670
00:37:59,327 --> 00:37:59,960
OHH!

671
00:37:59,961 --> 00:38:02,463
LISTEN. DO ME A FAVOR...

672
00:38:02,463 --> 00:38:04,331
[TALKING QUIETLY]

673
00:38:09,971 --> 00:38:12,473
EXCUSE ME.
DETECTIVE YERXA, RIGHT?

674
00:38:12,473 --> 00:38:13,724
YEAH.

675
00:38:13,724 --> 00:38:14,975
CARLA ENGEL, KCEI-TV.

676
00:38:14,976 --> 00:38:16,227
OH, RIGHT.
YEAH, YOU COVERED THE CARLSON CASE.

677
00:38:16,227 --> 00:38:17,478
VERY GOOD.

678
00:38:17,478 --> 00:38:18,729
DOING A STORY ON THIS?

679
00:38:18,729 --> 00:38:22,482
UH, NOT EXACTLY.
DO YOU THINK THE DOCTOR HAD SOMETHING TO DO WITH IT?

680
00:38:22,483 --> 00:38:26,236
SADOWSKI SAYS HE WAS
AT A CONFERENCE IN ALBUQUERQUE LAST NIGHT.

681
00:38:26,237 --> 00:38:27,488
I'D BE ASTONISHED
IF HE'D LIE ABOUT SOMETHING

682
00:38:27,488 --> 00:38:29,356
WE COULD EASILY CHECK
WITH A PHONE CALL...

683
00:38:29,357 --> 00:38:31,859
WHICH PHONE CALL
I'M ABOUT TO MAKE, IF YOU'LL EXCUSE ME.

684
00:38:31,859 --> 00:38:33,110
IS IT TRUE THAT ZAK
WAS BLINDFOLDED?

685
00:38:35,613 --> 00:38:37,498
YEAH.

686
00:38:37,498 --> 00:38:40,617
MAYBE THE KID WAS
PRACTICING THE STUFF THE DOC TAUGHT HIM.

687
00:38:40,618 --> 00:38:43,754
PRETTY CRAZY, THIS DOC,
IF YOU ASK ME.

688
00:38:43,754 --> 00:38:45,005
TAKE CARE.

689
00:38:50,628 --> 00:38:51,261
HEY.

690
00:38:51,262 --> 00:38:53,764
HEY.

691
00:38:53,764 --> 00:38:56,883
I'M SORRY ABOUT ZAK.

692
00:38:56,884 --> 00:38:59,386
WELL, HE KNEW THE RISK.
WE ALL DID.

693
00:38:59,387 --> 00:39:00,638
RIGHT?

694
00:39:00,638 --> 00:39:01,889
RIGHT.

695
00:39:01,889 --> 00:39:03,774
LET'S GO.

696
00:39:03,774 --> 00:39:05,642
Woman: YEAH, I'LL--
I'LL TAKE CARE OF THAT.

697
00:39:13,150 --> 00:39:16,286
WHEN ONE FALLS IN LIFE...

698
00:39:16,287 --> 00:39:18,789
THERE ARE 2 POSSIBILITIES:

699
00:39:18,789 --> 00:39:20,657
EITHER ONE CANNOT GET UP,

700
00:39:20,658 --> 00:39:25,045
OR ONE GETS UP AS BEST
ONE CAN AND MOVES FORWARD.

701
00:39:25,046 --> 00:39:28,165
THOSE WHO CANNOT GET UP...

702
00:39:28,799 --> 00:39:30,667
ARE KNOWN AS BABIES,

703
00:39:30,668 --> 00:39:34,421
THE ELDERLY, COWARDS,
OR THE DEAD!

704
00:39:35,056 --> 00:39:38,809
THE PEOPLE WHO GET UP
ARE KNOWN AS WARRIORS.

705
00:39:38,809 --> 00:39:43,180
ANYBODY HERE WHO CONSIDERS
HIMSELF OR HERSELF AMONG THE FORMER,

706
00:39:43,180 --> 00:39:44,431
PLEASE RAISE YOUR HAND.

707
00:39:48,185 --> 00:39:50,687
AND WHO HERE CONSIDERS
HIMSELF OR HERSELF A WARRIOR?

708
00:40:12,960 --> 00:40:15,462
LET'S SEE IF THAT'S SO.

