00:40:15,463 --> 00:40:16,096
Sadowski: COME ON, COME ON.

710
00:40:16,097 --> 00:40:21,435
COME ON. ONE STEP
AT A TIME. COME ON.

711
00:40:21,435 --> 00:40:25,188
DON'T THINK ABOUT
WHERE YOU ARE. THINK ABOUT MY VOICE.

712
00:40:25,189 --> 00:40:26,440
COME ON.

713
00:40:30,811 --> 00:40:32,696
Sadowski: REMEMBER...

714
00:40:33,314 --> 00:40:36,450
ANY FEAR CAN BE OVERCOME
BY A GREATER FEAR.

715
00:40:36,450 --> 00:40:39,569
IF FLAMES WERE LICKING
AT YOUR BACK, YOU'D MOVE.

716
00:40:39,570 --> 00:40:42,072
IF YOUR CHILD WAS ABOUT
TO FALL OFF THAT EDGE,

717
00:40:42,072 --> 00:40:43,323
YOU'D BE THERE
IN A HEARTBEAT.

718
00:40:45,826 --> 00:40:47,711
ONE...

719
00:40:47,711 --> 00:40:48,962
COME ON, HALLIE.

720
00:40:52,716 --> 00:40:53,967
2...

721
00:40:55,836 --> 00:40:57,721
YOU CAN DO IT, HALLIE.
YOU DID IT BEFORE.

722
00:40:57,721 --> 00:41:01,474
UH...THAT WAS ANOTHER ROOF.
MUCH LOWER.

723
00:41:01,475 --> 00:41:02,726
THERE WAS A RAIL.

724
00:41:05,846 --> 00:41:08,348
LAST TIME WE HAD ZAK!

725
00:41:08,349 --> 00:41:10,234
DON'T THINK ABOUT ZAK!

726
00:41:12,102 --> 00:41:17,107
I CAN'T HELP IT. OHH!

727
00:41:21,495 --> 00:41:23,363
3.

728
00:41:23,364 --> 00:41:25,866
[HALLIE SOBS]

729
00:41:28,369 --> 00:41:30,871
I'M SORRY, HALLIE.

730
00:41:40,264 --> 00:41:42,766
LAST TIME YOU MADE IT
OUT TO THE PIPE.

731
00:41:43,384 --> 00:41:45,269
NO, I CAN'T.

732
00:41:52,776 --> 00:41:55,278
ARE YOU GOING TO LET
WHAT HAPPENED TO ZAK

733
00:41:55,279 --> 00:41:59,032
RUIN EVERYTHING
THAT WE WORKED FOR?

734
00:41:59,033 --> 00:42:02,152
HMM? YOU KNOW WHAT
ZAK WOULD BE DOING IF HE WERE HERE?

735
00:42:02,152 --> 00:42:04,654
HE'D BE DANCING ON
THE EDGE OF THIS ROOF,

736
00:42:04,655 --> 00:42:06,540
LAUGHING AT YOU!

737
00:42:06,540 --> 00:42:08,408
HE'D BE ASHAMED OF YOU!

738
00:42:08,409 --> 00:42:12,162
YOU MAKE A MOCKERY
OF HIS DEATH!

739
00:42:17,167 --> 00:42:19,052
OR IS IT SOMETHING ELSE?

740
00:42:19,053 --> 00:42:24,675
YOU THINK MAYBE I HAD
SOMETHING TO DO WITH WHAT HAPPENED TO ZAK?

741
00:42:24,675 --> 00:42:26,560
DO YOU?!

742
00:42:26,560 --> 00:42:27,811
I DON'T THINK YOU DID IT.

743
00:42:28,429 --> 00:42:31,565
YEAH, BUT YOU'RE
NOT SURE, ARE YOU?

744
00:42:31,565 --> 00:42:35,318
AND THAT TINY LITTLE
SHADOW OF A DOUBT, NO MATTER HOW SMALL,

745
00:42:35,319 --> 00:42:39,690
WILL BE THE RUINATION
OF EVERYTHING THAT WE'VE WORKED FOR.

746
00:42:39,690 --> 00:42:42,192
BECAUSE IF YOU DON'T
TRUST ME COMPLETELY,

747
00:42:42,192 --> 00:42:44,077
IT'S OVER.

748
00:42:44,078 --> 00:42:46,580
RIGHT HERE, RIGHT NOW!

749
00:43:12,856 --> 00:43:15,975
Sadowski:
FEAR CAN'T HURT YOU UNLESS YOU SURRENDER TO IT.

750
00:43:15,976 --> 00:43:17,861
ONCE YOU DO...

751
00:43:17,861 --> 00:43:19,112
IT CAN KILL YOU.

752
00:44:58,579 --> 00:45:02,332
COME ON, DOC.

753
00:45:02,332 --> 00:45:03,966
YOU CAN MAKE IT.

754
00:45:10,174 --> 00:45:12,676
Hallie: I CAN'T BELIEVE
YOU DID THAT.

755
00:45:12,676 --> 00:45:14,561
IT WASN'T ME.

756
00:45:14,561 --> 00:45:16,429
IT WAS LIKE I WAS
STANDING OUTSIDE MYSELF, WATCHING.

757
00:45:16,430 --> 00:45:18,932
OH, I SAW YOU MOVING FORWARD,
GETTING CLOSER TO THE EDGE.

758
00:45:18,932 --> 00:45:20,183
I THOUGHT YOU
WERE GOING TO JUMP.

759
00:45:20,184 --> 00:45:21,435
OH, SO DID I!

760
00:45:21,435 --> 00:45:23,937
OH, I WISH I COULD
HAVE SEEN US.

761
00:45:23,937 --> 00:45:27,690
WHEN SADOWSKI SAID
THAT WOULD BE THE END OF THE GROUP, I JUST...

762
00:45:27,691 --> 00:45:29,576
I SNAPPED, YOU KNOW?
I HAD TO DO SOMETHING.

763
00:45:29,576 --> 00:45:31,444
I SAW MY WHOLE LIFE
FLASH BEFORE MY EYES.

764
00:45:31,445 --> 00:45:32,696
I JUST KEPT THINKING
ABOUT MY KIDS.

765
00:45:33,330 --> 00:45:34,581
THAT'S WHAT GOT ME
OUT ON THE ROOF.

766
00:45:34,581 --> 00:45:35,832
HOW MANY KIDS YOU GOT?

767
00:45:35,833 --> 00:45:37,701
UMM, 3.

768
00:45:37,701 --> 00:45:39,586
PICTURES, PICTURES.

769
00:45:39,586 --> 00:45:40,203
YES, YES. HERE.

770
00:45:40,204 --> 00:45:43,340
THEY DON'T TALK TO
ME ANYMORE, THOUGH.

771
00:45:43,340 --> 00:45:44,591
WHY NOT?

772
00:45:44,591 --> 00:45:47,710
OH, WELL, THE LAST
COUPLE OF YEARS GOT SO BAD

773
00:45:47,711 --> 00:45:49,596
I WOULDN'T EVEN COME UP
OUT OF THE BASEMENT.

774
00:45:49,596 --> 00:45:52,715
THAT'S WHEN THEY
SENT ME TO GREENDALE.

775
00:45:52,716 --> 00:45:57,103
2 YEARS, STRAIGHTJACKET,
HELMET, WHOLE 9 YARDS.

776
00:45:57,104 --> 00:46:01,475
BUT...THEY KEEP ME
GOING.

777
00:46:01,475 --> 00:46:04,561
IF I DIDN'T EVER THINK
I'D SEE THEM AGAIN, SOMETIME, SOMEHOW,

778
00:46:04,561 --> 00:46:05,812
I'D END IT ALL TOMORROW.

779
00:46:10,200 --> 00:46:11,451
DO YOU HAVE ANY KIDS?

780
00:46:11,452 --> 00:46:15,205
AH, NO...NOT YET.

781
00:46:17,074 --> 00:46:20,210
BUT WHEN I DO...

782
00:46:20,210 --> 00:46:23,329
I HOPE THEY LOOK
LIKE HIM.

783
00:46:23,330 --> 00:46:25,832
OH, MY GOODNESS.

784
00:46:25,833 --> 00:46:27,084
MMM...OOH, WHAT A HUNK!

785
00:46:27,084 --> 00:46:27,717
WHERE WAS THAT TAKEN?

786
00:46:28,335 --> 00:46:30,220
Carla: UH, BERMUDA.

787
00:46:30,220 --> 00:46:31,471
WE MET LAST AUGUST.

788
00:46:31,472 --> 00:46:32,723
MY SISTER
AND I WENT THERE AFTER MY PARENTS DIED,

789
00:46:32,723 --> 00:46:35,225
AND MARK WAS DOING
A PHOTO SHOOT,

790
00:46:35,225 --> 00:46:38,344
AND, ACTUALLY,
RACHEL MET HIM FIRST. SHE INTRODUCED US.

791
00:46:38,345 --> 00:46:40,847
WELL, YOU LOOK
GREAT TOGETHER.

792
00:46:53,360 --> 00:46:57,747
♪ ...WHO WILL
TAKE OUR LAST CHANCES ♪

793
00:46:59,616 --> 00:47:04,621
♪ WHO WILL UNMAKE THINGS
GONE WRONG ♪

794
00:47:04,621 --> 00:47:06,506
Rachel: CRANK IT UP,
CRANK IT UP! I LOVE THIS SONG.

795
00:47:06,507 --> 00:47:11,512
♪ WHO WILL
TAKE OUR LAST CHANCES... ♪

796
00:47:14,014 --> 00:47:16,066
YOU CAN'T LET GO OF ME!

797
00:47:18,719 --> 00:47:21,138
AAH!

798
00:47:57,424 --> 00:47:58,675
AAH!

799
00:47:58,675 --> 00:48:02,428
HEY, IT'S ONLY ME.
WH-WHAT'S THE MATTER?

800
00:48:05,566 --> 00:48:07,434
I'M SO SCARED.

801
00:48:07,434 --> 00:48:09,319
I THINK RACHEL'S
STALKING ME.

802
00:48:09,319 --> 00:48:12,438
WHAT?

803
00:48:12,439 --> 00:48:14,324
THE SCARF.

804
00:48:14,324 --> 00:48:16,192
WHAT SCARF?

805
00:48:16,193 --> 00:48:18,078
THAT SHE WAS WEARING
ON THE CLIFF.

806
00:48:18,078 --> 00:48:19,329
I PUT IT RIGHT HERE
THE OTHER DAY. WHERE IS IT NOW?

807
00:48:19,329 --> 00:48:21,831
I...MAYBE THE HOUSEKEEPER
PUT IT AWAY.

808
00:48:21,832 --> 00:48:23,700
NO, THE HOUSEKEEPER
DOESN'T COME TILL TOMORROW, MARK.

809
00:48:24,334 --> 00:48:26,202
RACHEL HAS IT.

810
00:48:26,203 --> 00:48:27,454
RACHEL HAS IT.
I SAW HER.

811
00:48:27,454 --> 00:48:30,590
SHE WAS WEARING IT.
I SAW IT ON HER TONIGHT!

812
00:48:32,459 --> 00:48:36,846
OH...

813
00:48:36,847 --> 00:48:40,600
I'M CRAZY.

814
00:48:40,601 --> 00:48:42,469
I'M CRAZY!

815
00:48:42,469 --> 00:48:46,222
YOU'RE NOT CRAZY, OK?

816
00:48:46,223 --> 00:48:48,108
YOU'RE JUST EXHAUSTED.

817
00:48:55,616 --> 00:48:59,369
COME ON. I GOT AN IDEA.

818
00:49:11,882 --> 00:49:14,384
I WANT YOU TO SAY
WHAT I SAY.

819
00:49:22,509 --> 00:49:25,011
RACHEL, I LOVED YOU
WITH ALL MY HEART.

820
00:49:28,148 --> 00:49:31,901
RACHEL, I LOVED YOU
WITH ALL MY HEART.

821
00:49:35,022 --> 00:49:38,775
AND I DID
EVERYTHING THAT I COULD TO SAVE YOU.

822
00:49:38,775 --> 00:49:44,413
AND I DID EVERYTHING
I COULD TO SAVE YOU.

823
00:49:44,414 --> 00:49:48,167
BUT NOW I HAVE TO GO ON
WITH MY LIFE

824
00:49:48,168 --> 00:49:51,921
AND PUT THIS TERRIBLE
PAIN BEHIND ME.

825
00:50:03,183 --> 00:50:05,685
MAYBE THAT DOCTOR IS...

826
00:50:06,303 --> 00:50:08,188
PUSHING YOU TOO FAST.

827
00:50:08,188 --> 00:50:10,690
[SIGHS]

828
00:50:10,691 --> 00:50:14,444
THIS GROUP IS MY ONLY HOPE
OF GETTING BETTER.

829
00:50:14,444 --> 00:50:15,695
YES, BUT--

830
00:50:15,696 --> 00:50:16,947
I'M NOT GOING
TO LEAVE IT, MARK.

831
00:50:16,947 --> 00:50:18,815
CARLA...

832
00:50:50,097 --> 00:50:51,982
[DOORBELL RINGS]

833
00:50:52,599 --> 00:50:55,101
MARK, JUST LEAVE IT.
JUST LEAVE IT.

834
00:50:55,102 --> 00:50:58,238
[DOORBELL RINGS]

835
00:51:03,860 --> 00:51:05,745
I SHOULD GET IT.

836
00:51:05,746 --> 00:51:08,248
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

837
00:51:12,002 --> 00:51:13,253
[DOORBELL RINGS]

838
00:51:15,122 --> 00:51:17,624
SORRY TO DISTURB YOU,
SIR. DETECTIVE YERXA.

839
00:51:17,624 --> 00:51:18,875
IS YOUR WIFE IN?

840
00:51:18,875 --> 00:51:20,126
GOOD EVENING, MA'AM.

841
00:51:22,012 --> 00:51:23,880
I'M AFRAID I'M GOING TO
HAVE TO ASK YOU TO COME DOWN TO THE STATION.

842
00:51:23,880 --> 00:51:25,765
WHAT IS IT? WHAT'S WRONG?

843
00:51:25,766 --> 00:51:27,634
WE HAVE WHAT
LOOKS LIKE A SUICIDE,

844
00:51:27,634 --> 00:51:29,519
AND YOUR NAME APPEARS
AT THE SCENE.

845
00:51:29,519 --> 00:51:32,021
WHAT?!

846
00:51:32,022 --> 00:51:33,890
WRITTEN BY THE VICTIM...

847
00:51:33,890 --> 00:51:35,775
IN HER OWN BLOOD
BEFORE SHE DIED.

848
00:51:38,895 --> 00:51:40,146
WHO?

849
00:51:40,147 --> 00:51:42,649
Yerxa: A WOMAN BY THE
NAME OF HALLIE BARNES.

850
00:51:42,649 --> 00:51:45,151
HALLIE'S DEAD?

851
00:51:45,786 --> 00:51:47,654
YES, MA'AM.

852
00:51:47,654 --> 00:51:49,539
IT APPEARS SHE JUMPED
FROM THE ROOF OF HER APARTMENT BUILDING...

853
00:51:49,539 --> 00:51:50,790
3 STORIES.

854
00:51:50,791 --> 00:51:52,659
AMAZING SHE COULD WRITE
ANYTHING AT ALL.

855
00:51:57,314 --> 00:51:59,182
SHE EVER MENTION
THINKING ABOUT SUICIDE?

856
00:51:59,182 --> 00:52:01,067
SHE DID SAY
SHE MIGHT TRY IT

857
00:52:01,067 --> 00:52:02,935
IF SHE COULDN'T
GET HER KIDS BACK,

858
00:52:02,936 --> 00:52:04,821
BUT I'M SURE
SHE WASN'T ACTUALLY THINKING ABOUT IT.

859
00:52:04,821 --> 00:52:07,323
YOU'D BE SURPRISED AT
WHAT PEOPLE THINK ABOUT.

860
00:52:07,324 --> 00:52:10,443
THEN AGAIN,
IF THERE WAS FOUL PLAY,

861
00:52:10,443 --> 00:52:12,945
THE LAST THING SHE DID
WAS WRITE YOUR NAME,

862
00:52:12,946 --> 00:52:13,579
WHICH MIGHT BE
SIGNIFICANT.

863
00:52:13,580 --> 00:52:16,032
I WAS HER FRIEND,
FOR GOD'S SAKES.

864
00:52:16,032 --> 00:52:17,283
WAIT A SECOND.

865
00:52:17,284 --> 00:52:19,169
IF ANYBODY COULD'VE GOTTEN
HER OUT ON THAT ROOF,

866
00:52:19,169 --> 00:52:21,037
IT WOULD HAVE BEEN
DR. SADOWSKI.

867
00:52:21,037 --> 00:52:22,254
WE'RE LOOKING INTO THAT.

868
00:52:25,375 --> 00:52:27,877
SHE WAS BLINDFOLDED,
YOU KNOW.

869
00:52:27,878 --> 00:52:30,380
SHE WAS?

870
00:52:30,380 --> 00:52:33,516
MM-HMM. SAME AS THAT KID
ON CLARKE TOWER.

871
00:52:33,517 --> 00:52:36,636
YOU KNEW HIM, TOO, RIGHT?

872
00:52:40,390 --> 00:52:44,777
SEE, THIS IS THE ONE
WE TOOK OFF HIM COUPLE DAYS AGO.

873
00:52:44,778 --> 00:52:49,149
AND HERE'S THE ONE FROM
HALLIE BARNES LAST NIGHT.

874
00:52:49,149 --> 00:52:51,651
LOOKS PRETTY SIMILAR,
DON'T IT?

875
00:52:51,651 --> 00:52:56,038
FACT IS, LAB SAYS THEY'RE
THE VERY SAME KIND OF CLOTH.

876
00:52:57,908 --> 00:53:01,661
THAT ISN'T EVEN
THE MOST INTERESTING THING.

877
00:53:14,174 --> 00:53:14,807
SEE?

878
00:53:16,059 --> 00:53:17,310
THIS IS MINE.

879
00:53:21,681 --> 00:53:24,183
AAH!

880
00:53:29,823 --> 00:53:32,325
MY, MY, MY.

881
00:53:32,325 --> 00:53:34,193
GET HER SOME WATER.

882
00:53:34,194 --> 00:53:36,079
SHE HAVE A HISTORY
OF THAT?

883
00:53:36,079 --> 00:53:37,947
YOU GOT A HISTORY
OF BEING AN IDIOT?

884
00:53:39,833 --> 00:53:41,701
ARE YOU ACCUSING HER?

885
00:53:41,701 --> 00:53:43,586
HUH?

886
00:53:43,587 --> 00:53:47,340
'CAUSE IF YOU ARE,
JUST COME OUT AND SAY SO, OK?

887
00:53:47,340 --> 00:53:49,842
I'M JUST POINTING OUT
SOMETHING INTERESTING HERE.

888
00:53:49,843 --> 00:53:52,345
SHE'S A MEMBER
OF THE PRESS, NO?

889
00:53:52,345 --> 00:53:54,213
I MADE NO ACCUSATIONS
THAT I RECALL.

890
00:53:54,214 --> 00:53:55,465
IS SHE UNDER ARREST?

891
00:53:55,465 --> 00:53:56,716
CERTAINLY NOT.

892
00:53:58,602 --> 00:53:59,853
FACT IS,
THERE'S NO EVIDENCE

893
00:53:59,853 --> 00:54:01,721
THAT ANYBODY WAS
ON THAT ROOF WITH HER.

894
00:54:01,721 --> 00:54:03,606
NO SIGN OF STRUGGLE.

895
00:54:03,607 --> 00:54:06,109
NO MARKS
ON THE LADY'S BODY,

896
00:54:06,109 --> 00:54:07,977
EXCEPT FOR IMPACT
WITH CONCRETE,

897
00:54:07,978 --> 00:54:11,114
I'LL PROBABLY WRITE IT UP
AS A SUICIDE.

898
00:54:13,617 --> 00:54:18,622
IT'S JUST THAT HER NAME
WAS RIGHT THERE ON THE SIDEWALK.

899
00:54:22,993 --> 00:54:24,244
RACHEL IS DEAD.

900
00:54:24,244 --> 00:54:26,129
YOU'VE GOT TO START
ACCEPTING THAT OR--

901
00:54:26,129 --> 00:54:27,380
OR WHAT?

902
00:54:27,380 --> 00:54:29,882
I'LL GO CRAZY
LIKE MY MOTHER?

903
00:54:29,883 --> 00:54:33,002
NO. THAT IS NOT
WHAT I MEANT.

904
00:54:33,003 --> 00:54:36,139
CAN'T YOU SEE THAT
RACHEL IS OUT THERE?

905
00:54:36,139 --> 00:54:39,892
SHE'S ALWAYS
DISTRUSTED ME.

906
00:54:39,893 --> 00:54:42,979
EVER SINCE WE WERE KIDS.

907
00:54:42,979 --> 00:54:46,682
AND NOW THAT I LET HER FALL,
SHE'LL NEVER FORGIVE ME.

908
00:54:46,683 --> 00:54:49,185
CARLA, COME ON.
YOU GOTTA FIGHT THIS.

909
00:54:49,185 --> 00:54:52,938
I HAVE LIFE,
AND RACHEL DOESN'T...

910
00:54:53,573 --> 00:54:54,824
AND IT'S MY FAULT.

911
00:54:56,693 --> 00:54:59,195
SHE'LL NEVER LET ME REST.

912
00:55:00,947 --> 00:55:02,832
SHE'LL KILL EVERYONE I LOVE

913
00:55:02,832 --> 00:55:06,585
AND THEN TEAR ME DOWN
WITH HER.

914
00:55:11,591 --> 00:55:12,842
I WANT YOU
TO QUIT THE GROUP.

915
00:55:13,460 --> 00:55:14,711
NO, I WILL NOT
QUIT THE GROUP!

916
00:55:14,711 --> 00:55:18,464
NO. LISTEN, HOW WELL
DO YOU REALLY KNOW THESE PEOPLE?

917
00:55:18,465 --> 00:55:20,350
BY NOW YOU ALL HAVE
EACH OTHER'S

918
00:55:20,350 --> 00:55:22,218
PHONE NUMBERS
AND ADDRESSES.

919
00:55:22,218 --> 00:55:23,469
YEAH.

920
00:55:23,470 --> 00:55:25,972
THE HOUSE WAS OPEN
ALL DAY WHEN I WAS AT MY STUDIO.

921
00:55:25,972 --> 00:55:29,108
SOMEBODY WHO KNEW YOU,
WHO KNEW YOUR STORY,

922
00:55:29,109 --> 00:55:30,360
KNEW YOUR VULNERABILITY,

923
00:55:30,360 --> 00:55:34,080
COULD EASILY
HAVE GOTTEN IN HERE TO TAKE THAT SCARF.

924
00:55:34,080 --> 00:55:36,565
[TELEPHONE RINGS]

925
00:55:39,069 --> 00:55:40,954
[RING]

926
00:55:40,954 --> 00:55:41,571
HELLO.

927
00:55:44,074 --> 00:55:46,576
IT'S BEN FROM THE GROUP.

928
00:55:46,576 --> 00:55:47,827
HI, BEN.,@

929
00:55:47,827 --> 00:55:50,329
YEAH. HE QUESTIONED US
THIS MORNING.

930
00:55:50,330 --> 00:55:53,466
HE THINKS
IT'S A SUICIDE--

931
00:55:53,466 --> 00:55:55,968
WHAT--WHAT DO YOU--

932
00:55:56,586 --> 00:55:57,837
BEN, NO! BEN, WAIT!

933
00:55:57,837 --> 00:55:59,722
[HANGS UP]

934
00:56:04,094 --> 00:56:04,727
HE'S QUITTING.

935
00:56:04,728 --> 00:56:06,596
YEAH.

936
00:56:06,596 --> 00:56:07,847
SEE?

937
00:56:07,847 --> 00:56:09,732
I THINK THAT'S
THE RIGHT THING TO DO.

938
00:56:09,733 --> 00:56:11,601
MAYBE THAT'S
WHAT RACHEL WANTS.

939
00:56:11,601 --> 00:56:13,486
YOU KNOW,
TO ISOLATE ME.

940
00:56:14,104 --> 00:56:15,989
THAT IS CRAZY.

941
00:56:15,989 --> 00:56:17,857
WRONG WORD, MARK.

942
00:56:17,857 --> 00:56:19,108
WHERE YOU GOING?

943
00:56:19,109 --> 00:56:22,245
I HAVE TO TALK TO HIM.

944
00:56:22,245 --> 00:56:23,496
CARLA...

945
00:56:23,496 --> 00:56:24,747
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

946
00:56:27,751 --> 00:56:29,002
EXCUSE THE MESS.

947
00:56:29,619 --> 00:56:31,504
WANT ANY WATER
OR ANYTHING?

948
00:56:31,504 --> 00:56:32,755
NO.

949
00:56:32,756 --> 00:56:35,875
I CAN'T STAY LONG, BEN.

950
00:56:35,875 --> 00:56:37,126
LOOK, I JUST--

951
00:56:37,127 --> 00:56:39,012
I WANTED TO SEE YOU
FACE-TO-FACE AND TELL YOU

952
00:56:39,629 --> 00:56:40,880
YOU CAN'T
QUIT THE GROUP NOW.

953
00:56:40,880 --> 00:56:42,131
NO? WATCH THIS.

954
00:56:42,132 --> 00:56:45,885
BEN, PLEASE DON'T LET
HALLIE'S SUICIDE RUIN ALL WE'VE WORKED FOR.

955
00:56:45,885 --> 00:56:47,770
HALLIE WASN'T A SUICIDE.

956
00:56:47,771 --> 00:56:49,639
HOW DO YOU KNOW THAT?

957
00:56:49,639 --> 00:56:51,524
CAN'T TELL YOU.

958
00:56:51,524 --> 00:56:53,392
DID YOU TELL
DETECTIVE YERXA?

959
00:56:53,393 --> 00:56:54,026
I CAN'T.

960
00:56:54,027 --> 00:56:55,278
WHY?

961
00:56:55,278 --> 00:56:58,397
MAYBE BECAUSE I'M CRAZY.
I DON'T KNOW ANYMORE.

962
00:56:58,398 --> 00:57:00,283
I MEAN, LOOK AT ME.
I'M PACKING MY THINGS.

963
00:57:00,283 --> 00:57:01,534
I'M LEAVING.

964
00:57:01,534 --> 00:57:04,036
I DON'T EVEN KNOW
WHERE I'M GOING.

965
00:57:04,037 --> 00:57:06,539
MAYBE KANSAS. I UNDERSTAND
IT'S REALLY FLAT THERE.

966
00:57:06,539 --> 00:57:08,407
BEN, I'M NOT THE POLICE,
ALL RIGHT?

967
00:57:08,408 --> 00:57:10,293
I'M JUST YOUR FRIEND.
YOU CAN TELL ME.

968
00:57:10,293 --> 00:57:12,161
IT'S NOT THAT
I WANT TO QUIT.

969
00:57:12,162 --> 00:57:14,047
I DON'T HAVE ANY CHOICE.

970
00:57:14,047 --> 00:57:16,549
WHAT HAPPENED?

971
00:57:16,549 --> 00:57:18,417
I GOT A PHONE CALL.

972
00:57:18,418 --> 00:57:19,051
FROM WHO?

973
00:57:19,052 --> 00:57:20,920
I CAN'T TELL YOU.

974
00:57:20,920 --> 00:57:22,805
BEN, JUST TELL ME.

975
00:57:24,057 --> 00:57:27,176
DO YOU REMEMBER THE GUY
I TOLD YOU ABOUT FROM THE ARMY?

976
00:57:27,177 --> 00:57:29,679
YOUR FRIEND? THE ONE
WHOSE CHUTE DIDN'T OPEN?

977
00:57:29,679 --> 00:57:30,930
IT WAS HIM.

978
00:57:34,601 --> 00:57:35,234
YEAH.

979
00:57:39,606 --> 00:57:41,491
IVAN IRELAND HIMSELF.

980
00:57:42,108 --> 00:57:43,993
I THOUGHT YOU SAID
HE DIED.

981
00:57:44,611 --> 00:57:46,496
HE DID.

982
00:57:46,496 --> 00:57:48,998
THEN HOW
COULD HE CALL YOU?

983
00:57:48,998 --> 00:57:50,866
THAT'S A GOOD QUESTION,
AND YOU KNOW WHAT?

984
00:57:50,867 --> 00:57:52,752
I'M NOT HANGING AROUND
TO FIND OUT THE ANSWER.

985
00:57:52,752 --> 00:57:54,003
BEN, YOUR FRIEND
IS DEAD, ALL RIGHT?

986
00:57:54,003 --> 00:57:55,871
DEAD PEOPLE
DON'T MAKE PHONE CALLS.

987
00:57:55,872 --> 00:57:57,123
I KNOW THAT!

988
00:57:57,123 --> 00:57:59,008
MAYBE EVEN
YOU KNOW THAT,

989
00:57:59,008 --> 00:58:02,127
BUT APPARENTLY
HE DOESN'T KNOW THAT 'CAUSE IT WAS HIM.

990
00:58:02,128 --> 00:58:04,013
HE KNEW EVERYTHING
ABOUT THE PLANE.

991
00:58:04,013 --> 00:58:05,264
HE KNEW ALL THE DETAILS,

992
00:58:05,265 --> 00:58:07,767
AND HE KNEW WHAT I
WAS DOING HERE, TOO.

993
00:58:07,767 --> 00:58:10,886
HE EVEN TOLD ME
ABOUT HALLIE BEFORE THE POLICE EVER CAME.

994
00:58:12,772 --> 00:58:14,023
tw
WHAT...

995
00:58:14,023 --> 00:58:15,891
WHAT ABOUT HALLIE?

996
00:58:15,892 --> 00:58:17,777
HE TOLD ME SHE WAS DEAD.

997
00:58:20,280 --> 00:58:21,531
HE KNOWS
WHO KILLED HER, TOO.

998
00:58:21,531 --> 00:58:24,650
SOMEONE FROM HIS SIDE,
HE SAID.

999
00:58:24,651 --> 00:58:27,153
SAID HE DOESN'T
KNOW HER NAME OR WHAT SHE LOOKS LIKE

1000
00:58:27,153 --> 00:58:29,038
BECAUSE SHE KEEPS
HER FACE ALL COVERED.

1001
00:58:29,038 --> 00:58:31,540
BUT SHE'S
A FELLOW FALLER.

1002
00:58:33,376 --> 00:58:35,878
HE WANTS TO MAKE ME
SUFFER FOR WHAT I DID.

1003
00:58:35,879 --> 00:58:37,747
JUST LIKE THE GIRL
IN THE SCARF

1004
00:58:37,747 --> 00:58:40,249
WANTS THE ONE THAT'S
RESPONSIBLE FOR HER FALLING TO SUFFER.

1005
00:58:40,250 --> 00:58:42,752
GIRL IN THE SCARF?

1006
00:58:42,752 --> 00:58:47,039
YEAH. HE SAID
HE KEEPS HER FACE COVERED

1007
00:58:47,040 --> 00:58:48,875
BECAUSE IT'S
ALL BROKEN AWAY FROM THE ROCKS.

1008
00:58:50,743 --> 00:58:52,628
Rachel:
YOU CAN'T LET GO OF ME!

1009
00:58:56,382 --> 00:58:57,633
BEN...

1010
00:58:57,634 --> 00:59:00,753
I CANNOT EXPLAIN
WHAT'S HAPPENING.

1011
00:59:00,753 --> 00:59:02,004
I JUST KNOW...

1012
00:59:02,005 --> 00:59:05,141
WE NEED THE GROUP.

1013
00:59:05,141 --> 00:59:07,009
YOU CAN'T QUIT.

1014
00:59:07,010 --> 00:59:08,895
WE NEED EACH OTHER.

1015
00:59:08,895 --> 00:59:12,648
YOU, ME, AND JOCELYN.

1016
00:59:12,649 --> 00:59:15,151
I JUST SPOKE TO JOCELYN.
SHE'S QUIT, TOO.

1017
00:59:15,151 --> 00:59:19,522
Young Rachel:
♪ CARLA, JOIN ME ♪

1018
00:59:19,522 --> 00:59:20,773
♪ CARLA ♪

1019
00:59:21,407 --> 00:59:22,591
SO, HOW DID YOU FIND ME?

1020
00:59:22,592 --> 00:59:24,477
I WENT TO YOUR HOUSE.
SOMEONE HELD UP A NOTE.

1021
00:59:24,477 --> 00:59:26,345
THAT WAS MY MOM.
SHE HASN'T TALKED IN 5 YEARS.

1022
00:59:26,346 --> 00:59:28,848
SHE'S PHOBIC
ABOUT EVERYTHING, INCLUDING PEOPLE.

1023
00:59:28,848 --> 00:59:30,733
LOOK, JOCELYN,
WE HAVE TO TALK ABOUT--

1024
00:59:30,733 --> 00:59:32,601
LOOK, I DON'T BELIEVE
IN GHOSTS.

1025
00:59:33,236 --> 00:59:35,104
I DON'T KNOW
WHAT HAPPENED TO ZAK,

1026
00:59:35,738 --> 00:59:36,989
BUT HALLIE
KILLED HERSELF.

1027
00:59:36,990 --> 00:59:38,241
AND I KNOW WHY.

1028
00:59:38,241 --> 00:59:41,360
SAME REASON I TRIED
LAST YEAR.

1029
00:59:41,361 --> 00:59:43,863
I JUMPED OUT OF
A THIRD STORY WINDOW.

1030
00:59:43,863 --> 00:59:46,365
SPENT 8 MONTHS
IN THE HOSPITAL.

1031
00:59:46,366 --> 00:59:48,251
RIGHT NOW I FEEL LIKE
I COULD DO IT AGAIN.

1032
00:59:48,251 --> 00:59:50,753
LOOK, JOCELYN, I DON'T SEE
HOW HALLIE COULD'VE DONE THAT.

1033
00:59:50,753 --> 00:59:53,872
WELL, WHEN YOU'RE
DESPERATE, YOU DO IT.

1034
00:59:53,873 --> 00:59:57,626
IT GOT SO BAD
THAT I'D GO TO BED AND PRAY, "PLEASE, GOD,

1035
00:59:57,627 --> 00:59:59,512
DON'T LET ME WAKE UP
IN THE MORNING."

1036
00:59:59,512 --> 01:00:02,014
I MEAN, WHAT WAS I
LIVING FOR?

1037
01:00:02,015 --> 01:00:04,217
TO KEEP MY MOTHER
OUT OF AN INSTITUTION?

1038
01:00:04,217 --> 01:00:04,850
TO KEEP MYSELF OUT?

1039
01:00:04,851 --> 01:00:06,102
YOU'RE GETTING BETTER,
RIGHT?

1040
01:00:06,102 --> 01:00:07,970
AND HALLIE WAS
GETTING BETTER, TOO.

1041
01:00:07,971 --> 01:00:09,222
WELL, IF YOU STOP NOW,

1042
01:00:09,222 --> 01:00:10,473
YOU'RE JUST
GONNA BE RIGHT BACK WHERE YOU STARTED.

1043
01:00:10,473 --> 01:00:12,975
I DON'T KNOW!

1044
01:00:12,976 --> 01:00:17,363
WHAT I DO KNOW IS
THAT I DON'T WANT TO END UP LIKE MY MOTHER.

1045
01:00:17,363 --> 01:00:19,231
AND I DON'T WANT TO DIE.

1046
01:00:19,232 --> 01:00:20,483
YOU DON'T HAVE TO.

1047
01:00:20,483 --> 01:00:22,985
WE CAN BEAT THIS THING.

1048
01:00:22,986 --> 01:00:24,237
I'M SCARED, CARLA.

1049
01:00:24,871 --> 01:00:26,122
I'M SCARED, TOO, JOCELYN!

1050
01:00:26,122 --> 01:00:28,624
THIS IS NO WAY TO LIVE.

1051
01:00:28,625 --> 01:00:30,493
WE CANNOT QUIT NOW.

1052
01:00:32,996 --> 01:00:36,132
JOCELYN,
WE COULD DO THIS.

1053
01:00:39,252 --> 01:00:40,503
DEAL?

1054
01:00:44,891 --> 01:00:46,142
DEAL.

1055
01:00:46,142 --> 01:00:47,393
I APPRECIATE
WHAT YOU'RE SAYING,

1056
01:00:48,011 --> 01:00:49,262
BUT I'VE
MADE UP MY MIND.

1057
01:00:49,262 --> 01:00:50,513
WHY? BECAUSE
THERE'S ONLY 2 OF US?

1058
01:00:50,513 --> 01:00:52,398
NO, IT'S NOT THAT.

1059
01:00:52,398 --> 01:00:54,900
BUT I CAN'T PUT YOU OR
MY REPUTATION AT RISK

1060
01:00:55,518 --> 01:00:57,403
WHILE SOMEBODY'S TRYING
TO SABOTAGE MY WORK.

1061
01:00:57,403 --> 01:00:58,654
WHO WOULD HATE YOU
THAT MUCH?

1062
01:00:58,655 --> 01:00:59,906
I DON'T KNOW.

1063
01:00:59,906 --> 01:01:02,408
COULD BE A COLLEAGUE
WHO WANTS TO SEE ME FAIL.

1064
01:01:03,026 --> 01:01:04,277
COULD BE
A FORMER PATIENT.

1065
01:01:04,277 --> 01:01:07,413
BUT YOU'RE PUTTING US
AT RISK BY QUITTING.

1066
01:01:08,031 --> 01:01:09,282
I WOULD BE DEAD NOW
IF IT WASN'T FOR YOU.

1067
01:01:09,282 --> 01:01:10,533
SO WOULD I.

1068
01:01:10,533 --> 01:01:13,035
YOU KNOW WHAT?
HALLIE IS DEAD BECAUSE OF ME.

1069
01:01:13,036 --> 01:01:14,287
WHAT HAPPENED
TO ZAK,

1070
01:01:14,287 --> 01:01:14,920
ALSO BECAUSE
OF ME.

1071
01:01:15,538 --> 01:01:19,291
WHAT ABOUT
THE PHONE CALL TO BEN?

1072
01:01:19,292 --> 01:01:21,177
WELL, I DON'T THINK
ANYBODY CALLED BEN.

1073
01:01:21,177 --> 01:01:24,296
I THINK THAT WAS
JUST AN EXCUSE TO QUIT THE GROUP

1074
01:01:24,297 --> 01:01:25,548
OR TO GET OUT OF TOWN

1075
01:01:25,548 --> 01:01:28,050
BEFORE THE POLICE
START ASKING TOO MANY QUESTIONS.

1076
01:01:28,051 --> 01:01:30,553
I SAW BEN.
HE WAS TERRIFIED.

1077
01:01:30,553 --> 01:01:34,940
MM-HMM. WELL, BEN'S GOOD
AT BEING AFRAID.

1078
01:01:34,941 --> 01:01:38,060
HE ALSO HATED ZAK.

1079
01:01:38,061 --> 01:01:40,563
NOTHING'S IMPOSSIBLE
TO ME ANYMORE.

1080
01:01:40,563 --> 01:01:43,699
YOU TOLD US IF WE
FACED OUR WORST TERROR, WE WOULD BE CURED.

1081
01:01:43,700 --> 01:01:45,568
IT WAS JUST
A MATTER OF TIME

1082
01:01:45,568 --> 01:01:47,453
BEFORE SOMEBODY
ELSE GETS HURT.

1083
01:01:48,071 --> 01:01:50,573
THEN LET'S NOT
WASTE ANY TIME.

1084
01:01:50,573 --> 01:01:53,075
LET'S GO FOR BROKE.
NO HALF-MEASURES.

1085
01:01:53,076 --> 01:01:54,961
YOU'RE HARDLY READY
FOR THAT.

1086
01:01:54,961 --> 01:01:56,829
I'M TELLING YOU,
WE ARE.

1087
01:01:58,081 --> 01:01:59,966
I'LL GO FIRST.

1088
01:02:08,057 --> 01:02:09,925
IT'D BE YOUR
WORST NIGHTMARE.

1089
01:02:13,062 --> 01:02:14,930
FEAR CAN'T HURT ME, RIGHT?

1090
01:02:24,107 --> 01:02:26,609
Dr. Sadowski:
YOU READY IN THE BOAT?

1091
01:02:26,609 --> 01:02:29,745
WE'RE ALL SET.
WE'RE READY AND WAITING.

1092
01:02:34,117 --> 01:02:36,002
STEP OUT
ON THAT PLATFORM.

1093
01:02:36,619 --> 01:02:39,121
[PANTING]

1094
01:02:39,122 --> 01:02:41,624
TAKE A STEP.

1095
01:02:42,258 --> 01:02:43,509
DO IT.

1096
01:02:44,127 --> 01:02:47,263
ALL RIGHT,
KEEP GOING.

1097
01:02:47,263 --> 01:02:48,514
KEEP GOING.

1098
01:02:48,514 --> 01:02:49,765
TAKE A STEP.

1099
01:02:49,766 --> 01:02:51,017
AND ANOTHER.

1100
01:02:51,017 --> 01:02:53,519
JOCELYN, MAKE ME PROUD.
YOU CAN DO IT.

1101
01:02:53,519 --> 01:02:55,387
COME ON, COME ON,
COME ON.

1102
01:02:55,388 --> 01:02:57,273
YOU CAN DO IT.

1103
01:02:57,273 --> 01:03:02,278
KEEP GOING.
KEEP GOING.

1104
01:03:02,278 --> 01:03:05,397
A LITTLE FARTHER.

1105
01:03:05,398 --> 01:03:06,649
YOU'RE THERE.

1106
01:03:16,659 --> 01:03:17,910
JUST PUSH ME!

1107
01:03:17,910 --> 01:03:19,795
NO!

1108
01:03:19,796 --> 01:03:21,664
YOU SAID YOU WANTED
TO DO IT, JOCELYN.

1109
01:03:21,664 --> 01:03:24,166
DO WHAT YOU
WANT TO DO.

1110
01:03:31,057 --> 01:03:32,308
LET'S GO, LET'S GO.

1111
01:03:46,606 --> 01:03:48,491
IT'S WORKING.

1112
01:03:50,359 --> 01:03:51,610
IT'S WORKING.

1113
01:03:54,113 --> 01:03:54,746
[STATIC]

1114
01:03:54,747 --> 01:03:56,615
Rachel: CARLA!

1115
01:03:57,250 --> 01:03:59,118
[LAUGHING]

1116
01:04:02,255 --> 01:04:04,123
CARLA!

1117
01:04:05,374 --> 01:04:07,259
I'M NOT AFRAID ANYMORE.

1118
01:04:11,013 --> 01:04:12,881
Rachel: CARLA!

1119
01:04:12,882 --> 01:04:14,133
JOCELYN!

1120
01:04:14,133 --> 01:04:16,018
JOCELYN,
DON'T DO IT!

1121
01:04:16,018 --> 01:04:19,137
HA HA HA HA!

1122
01:04:19,138 --> 01:04:21,023
I'M NOT AFRAID ANYMORE!

1123
01:04:21,023 --> 01:04:22,891
JOCELYN,
CAN YOU HEAR ME?

1124
01:04:22,892 --> 01:04:24,143
DO IT.

1125
01:04:24,143 --> 01:04:25,394
DON'T JUMP!

1126
01:04:25,394 --> 01:04:28,530
AH! I FEEL LIKE
I CAN DO ANYTHING!

1127
01:04:28,531 --> 01:04:29,782
DO IT, DO IT, DO IT.

1128
01:04:29,782 --> 01:04:31,650
DON'T DO IT!
DON'T JUMP!

1129
01:04:31,651 --> 01:04:32,284
AH!

1130
01:04:34,153 --> 01:04:37,289
AAH!

1131
01:04:44,163 --> 01:04:47,299
WHOO-HOO! YEAH!

1132
01:04:49,168 --> 01:04:50,419
WHOO!

1133
01:04:50,419 --> 01:04:51,670
Jocelyn: OH, I DID IT!

1134
01:04:51,671 --> 01:04:53,556
HA HA HA HA!

1135
01:04:53,556 --> 01:04:55,424
OH, YES! YES!

1136
01:04:56,676 --> 01:04:59,812
YOU DID IT, JOCELYN!

1137
01:04:59,812 --> 01:05:01,680
OH, LOOK AT ME, GIRL!

1138
01:05:01,681 --> 01:05:05,434
WHOO! AH HA HA HA!

1139
01:05:11,691 --> 01:05:14,827
IS THERE ANYWHERE ELSE
I CAN FIND INFORMATION ON THIS GUY?

1140
01:05:14,827 --> 01:05:16,695
WELL, I SUPPOSE IF YOU
HAD A TISSUE SAMPLE,

1141
01:05:16,696 --> 01:05:17,947
YOU COULD DO
A DNA TEST.

1142
01:05:17,947 --> 01:05:20,449
OTHERWISE, AT THIS POINT,

1143
01:05:20,449 --> 01:05:22,334
I WOULD WAGER THAT
YOU KNOW MORE ABOUT HIM THAN HIS MOTHER DOES.

1144
01:05:22,335 --> 01:05:24,837
WHAT EXACTLY
ARE YOU LOOKING FOR?

1145
01:05:24,837 --> 01:05:27,956
I DON'T KNOW.

1146
01:05:27,957 --> 01:05:29,208
SOMETHING.

1147
01:05:29,208 --> 01:05:31,710
Carla: HOW DO YOU FEEL?

1148
01:05:31,711 --> 01:05:33,596
Jocelyn: OHH!
IT WAS INCREDIBLE.

1149
01:05:33,596 --> 01:05:34,847
IT WAS SO AWESOME.

1150
01:05:34,847 --> 01:05:37,966
JUST WAIT AND SEE.
HA HA HA!

1151
01:05:39,218 --> 01:05:42,971
OK. I'LL GET THE CREDIT CARD,
YOU CHOOSE THE RESTAURANT.

1152
01:05:43,606 --> 01:05:44,857
AND DON'T SCRIMP.

1153
01:05:46,108 --> 01:05:47,976
I'M SORRY YOU HAVE
TO WAIT OUT HERE.

1154
01:05:48,611 --> 01:05:49,228
I UNDERSTAND.

1155
01:05:49,862 --> 01:05:51,730
MAYBE I'LL GET HER
TO COME TO THE WINDOW AND WAVE.

1156
01:05:51,731 --> 01:05:52,982
OK.

1157
01:06:02,375 --> 01:06:04,243
[RACHEL GIGGLING]

1158
01:06:53,676 --> 01:06:55,544
[GIGGLING]

1159
01:06:58,681 --> 01:07:01,133
AAH!

1160
01:07:36,635 --> 01:07:37,886
SHE FELL.

1161
01:07:39,138 --> 01:07:41,006
CARLA!

1162
01:07:41,006 --> 01:07:42,257
CARLA!

1163
01:07:49,765 --> 01:07:51,650
WHAT HAPPENED?

1164
01:07:51,650 --> 01:07:53,518
MY MOTHER.

1165
01:07:53,519 --> 01:07:54,152
SHE'S...

1166
01:07:54,153 --> 01:07:55,404
WHAT?

1167
01:07:55,404 --> 01:07:59,157
SHE FELL
IN THE BATHROOM.

1168
01:07:59,158 --> 01:08:00,409
SHE'S DEAD.

1169
01:08:00,409 --> 01:08:04,162
OH, I SHOULDN'T HAVE
LEFT HER ALONE!

1170
01:08:06,031 --> 01:08:08,533
IT HAD TO HAVE
BEEN AN ACCIDENT.

1171
01:08:09,168 --> 01:08:11,670
SHE WAS SO HAPPY FOR ME.

1172
01:08:11,670 --> 01:08:14,172
SHE KNEW WHAT
I WAS GONNA DO TODAY.

1173
01:08:14,173 --> 01:08:19,178
DO YOU KNOW WHAT I SAW
WHEN I FIRST WALKED INTO THE HOUSE?

1174
01:08:19,178 --> 01:08:23,549
IT WAS
RIGHT ON THE TABLE ON THE DINING ROOM.

1175
01:08:27,937 --> 01:08:29,188
Carla: THE ROSES
ARE BEAUTIFUL.

1176
01:08:29,188 --> 01:08:31,690
THEY ALWAYS WERE
HER FAVORITE FLOWER.

1177
01:08:32,308 --> 01:08:35,444
ALL SHE WROTE
ON THE CARD WAS...

1178
01:08:35,444 --> 01:08:37,312
"CONGRATULATIONS."

1179
01:08:51,527 --> 01:08:52,778
[DOOR CLOSES]

1180
01:08:52,778 --> 01:08:54,029
CARLA!

1181
01:08:55,281 --> 01:08:57,149
CARLA!

1182
01:08:58,400 --> 01:08:59,651
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

1183
01:09:01,537 --> 01:09:03,405
I KNOW YOU THINK
I'M CRAZY.

1184
01:09:03,405 --> 01:09:05,907
NO. I JUST ASKED YOU
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

1185
01:09:05,908 --> 01:09:07,793
WE NEVER IDENTIFIED
THE BODY PROPERLY.

1186
01:09:07,793 --> 01:09:09,661
HER FACE WAS
SO BADLY SMASHED,

1187
01:09:09,662 --> 01:09:10,913
YOU DON'T EVEN KNOW
IF IT WAS HER OR NOT.

1188
01:09:10,913 --> 01:09:14,049
IT'S VERY IMPORTANT TO KNOW
IF THIS IS HER OR NOT.

1189
01:09:16,552 --> 01:09:19,054
WHAT DO YOU THINK
YOU'RE GONNA FIND IN THERE?

1190
01:09:19,054 --> 01:09:20,922
I THOUGHT MAYBE I COULD
FIND HER GOLD FILLINGS,

1191
01:09:20,923 --> 01:09:23,425
BUT THEN I REALIZED
THAT THOSE PEOPLE AT THE CREMATORIUM,

1192
01:09:23,425 --> 01:09:24,676
THEY WOULD'VE STOLE THAT.

1193
01:09:24,677 --> 01:09:29,064
BUT THEN I REALIZED
THEY WOULD MISS THE PIN IN HER WRIST

1194
01:09:29,064 --> 01:09:31,566
THAT THE DOCTOR PUT IN
WHEN SHE BROKE IT.

1195
01:09:31,567 --> 01:09:32,818
IT'S NOT HERE.

1196
01:09:32,818 --> 01:09:34,069
SO?

1197
01:09:34,069 --> 01:09:34,686
THE TITANIUM,
IT WOULDN'T MELT.

1198
01:09:35,321 --> 01:09:39,074
OH, BUT EVEN IF IT WOULD,
THEY WOULDN'T WANT IT.

1199
01:09:42,828 --> 01:09:45,330
JUST WHAT IF
THIS ISN'T HER?

1200
01:09:45,331 --> 01:09:47,199
ALL RIGHT, WOULD YOU
LISTEN TO YOURSELF?

1201
01:09:47,199 --> 01:09:49,701
I'M TRYING TO
FIGURE THIS OUT, MARK.

1202
01:09:49,702 --> 01:09:51,587
I'M SEEING HER!

1203
01:09:51,587 --> 01:09:53,455
I'M HEARING HER!
WHY?

1204
01:09:53,455 --> 01:09:54,706
I MEAN, MAYBE...

1205
01:09:54,707 --> 01:09:59,712
MAYBE IF THIS ISN'T HER,
MAYBE SHE'S ALIVE.

1206
01:09:59,712 --> 01:10:02,848
NO!
SHE'S DEAD!

1207
01:10:02,848 --> 01:10:04,099
THEY HAVE THOUGHT
OF EVERYTHING.

1208
01:10:04,099 --> 01:10:06,601
MAYBE IT'S SADOWSKI.
MAYBE IT'S BEN.

1209
01:10:06,602 --> 01:10:07,853
I'VE EVEN THOUGHT
IT COULD BE YOU.

1210
01:10:07,853 --> 01:10:10,972
ANYTHING IS EASIER THAN
BELIEVING IT'S RACHEL.

1211
01:10:10,973 --> 01:10:13,475
HOW ELSE AM I GONNA
EXPLAIN ALL THIS?

1212
01:10:13,475 --> 01:10:16,611
YOU WANT AN EXPLANATION?
LOOK AT THIS.

1213
01:10:16,612 --> 01:10:17,863
LOOK AT IT.

1214
01:10:17,863 --> 01:10:20,365
YOUR DR. SADOWSKI IS NOT
WHO HE SAYS HE IS.

1215
01:10:20,366 --> 01:10:21,617
WHAT ARE YOU
TALKING ABOUT?

1216
01:10:21,617 --> 01:10:24,119
I FOUND OUT WHO HE WAS
BEFORE HE BECAME A DOCTOR.

1217
01:10:24,119 --> 01:10:26,621
SEE, LOOK, HE USED TO BE
A MOUNTAINEERING GUY.

1218
01:10:26,622 --> 01:10:29,124
AND ON HIS LAST TRIP,
HE TOOK A BUNCH OF PEOPLE UP TO MOUNT RAINIER,

1219
01:10:29,124 --> 01:10:31,626
AND NONE OF THEM CAME BACK.

1220
01:10:31,627 --> 01:10:32,878
EXCEPT FOR SADOWSKI.

1221
01:10:32,878 --> 01:10:37,249
AND THE REST OF THEM,
THEY FELL TO THEIR DEATHS

1222
01:10:37,249 --> 01:10:38,500
OFF A 3,500-FOOT CLIFF.

1223
01:10:38,500 --> 01:10:40,385
THIS SOUNDS
LIKE AN ACCIDENT--

1224
01:10:40,386 --> 01:10:42,254
MAYBE, OK?

1225
01:10:42,254 --> 01:10:44,139
BUT THE BEAUTY OF BEING
THE ONLY SURVIVOR

1226
01:10:44,757 --> 01:10:46,642
IS THAT YOU GET TO SAY
WHAT HAPPENED.

1227
01:10:46,642 --> 01:10:49,144
I THINK
THIS IS A SICK GUY

1228
01:10:49,144 --> 01:10:51,012
WHO NEEDS TO TAKE PEOPLE
UP TO HIGH PLACES

1229
01:10:51,013 --> 01:10:54,149
AND WATCH THEM SUFFER
AND POSSIBLY DIE.

1230
01:10:54,149 --> 01:10:56,017
THAT'S WHY HE NEEDS
DESPERATE PEOPLE.

1231
01:10:56,018 --> 01:10:57,903
PEOPLE WHO WILL DO
WHATEVER HE SAYS.

1232
01:10:57,903 --> 01:11:00,405
BUT HE CURED ZAK
AND JOCELYN.

1233
01:11:00,406 --> 01:11:02,274
THEN LOOK WHAT HE DID.

1234
01:11:02,274 --> 01:11:04,159
OK, MAYBE HE THINKS
THAT HE CURED ZAK.

1235
01:11:04,159 --> 01:11:05,410
MArYBE HE THINKS
HE'S HELPING JOCELYN.

1236
01:11:05,411 --> 01:11:06,662
BUT WHAT ABOUT
THE PHONE CALL?

1237
01:11:06,662 --> 01:11:09,164
HUH? SADOWSKI COULDN'T HAVE
KNOWN ALL THAT STUFF

1238
01:11:09,164 --> 01:11:10,415
THAT BEN SAID
THE GUY KNEW.

1239
01:11:10,416 --> 01:11:12,918
CARLA, YOU CAN EASILY
FIND THAT STUFF IN THE LIBRARY

1240
01:11:12,918 --> 01:11:14,169
OR IN MILITARY RECORDS.

1241
01:11:14,787 --> 01:11:18,540
LOOK WHAT I FOUND
IN JUST A COUPLE HOURS.

1242
01:11:21,677 --> 01:11:22,928
NO!

1243
01:11:24,179 --> 01:11:25,430
CARLA, OPEN YOUR EYES.

1244
01:11:25,431 --> 01:11:28,550
YOU WERE SO DESPERATE
TO BELIEVE THAT LUNATIC,

1245
01:11:28,550 --> 01:11:32,303
YOU CAN'T SEE WHAT'S
RIGHT IN FRONT OF YOUR FACE.

1246
01:11:32,304 --> 01:11:33,555
COME HERE.

1247
01:11:33,555 --> 01:11:34,806
JUST COME HERE.

1248
01:11:36,692 --> 01:11:37,309
SHH.

1249
01:11:38,560 --> 01:11:41,062
NOW, LISTEN TO ME.

1250
01:11:41,063 --> 01:11:44,199
MAYBE HE'S DANGEROUS,
MAYBE HE'S NOT,

1251
01:11:44,199 --> 01:11:47,318
BUT HE CAN'T BE
THE ONLY DOCTOR THAT CAN HELP YOU, OK?

1252
01:11:47,319 --> 01:11:49,204
WE WILL FIND
SOMEBODY ELSE.

1253
01:11:49,204 --> 01:11:49,821
WHERE?

1254
01:11:49,822 --> 01:11:51,707
I DON'T KNOW.

1255
01:11:51,707 --> 01:11:54,209
MOVE TO ANOTHER CITY,
I DON'T CARE, CARLA.

1256
01:11:54,827 --> 01:11:56,712
AS LONG AS YOU'RE SAFE.

1257
01:11:57,963 --> 01:12:03,585
NOW, I MADE SOME COPIES
OF THESE DOCUMENTS FOR THAT DETECTIVE.

1258
01:12:03,585 --> 01:12:06,087
BUT I WANT YOU TO
PROMISE ME SOMETHING.

1259
01:12:06,088 --> 01:12:11,726
PROMISE ME THAT YOU
WILL NOT GO SEE SADOWSKI IN THE MORNING, OK?

1260
01:12:11,727 --> 01:12:12,978
I PROMISE.

1261
01:12:16,732 --> 01:12:19,234
I LOVE YOU, CARLA.

1262
01:12:19,234 --> 01:12:22,353
AND I'M NOT GONNA
LOSE YOU.

1263
01:12:48,630 --> 01:12:50,465
[RACHEL'S FLUTE MUSIC]

1264
01:12:54,219 --> 01:12:56,721
[FLUTE]

1265
01:12:57,356 --> 01:13:01,727
Rachel: CARLA...

1266
01:13:01,727 --> 01:13:05,480
[FLUTE]

1267
01:13:29,888 --> 01:13:34,259
[FLUTE]

1268
01:13:48,023 --> 01:13:49,908
[FLUTE]

1269
01:13:51,160 --> 01:13:53,662
HA HA HA HA!

1270
01:14:00,536 --> 01:14:01,787
Rachel: CARLA!

1271
01:14:01,787 --> 01:14:03,672
NO.

1272
01:14:03,672 --> 01:14:04,923
NO.

1273
01:14:04,923 --> 01:14:06,791
HA HA HA!

1274
01:14:09,928 --> 01:14:11,179
Rachel: CARLA!

1275
01:14:13,048 --> 01:14:15,550
NO.

1276
01:14:15,551 --> 01:14:16,802
NO!

1277
01:14:18,053 --> 01:14:19,304
NO!

1278
01:14:51,220 --> 01:14:52,471
NO!

1279
01:14:54,890 --> 01:14:58,009
Rachel: HEE HEE HEE HEE!

1280
01:15:04,550 --> 01:15:07,653
YOU CAN'T LET GO OF ME!

1281
01:15:28,924 --> 01:15:30,175
CARLA!

1282
01:15:30,175 --> 01:15:32,043
[TELEPHONE RINGS]

1283
01:15:33,929 --> 01:15:35,180
HELLO.

1284
01:15:35,180 --> 01:15:37,048
HELLO. IS CARLA THERE?

1285
01:15:37,049 --> 01:15:38,300
WHO IS THIS?

1286
01:15:38,300 --> 01:15:40,185
UH, THIS IS DR. SADOWSKI.

1287
01:15:40,185 --> 01:15:41,436
MAY I SPEAK TO YOUR WIFE,
PLEASE?

1288
01:15:41,436 --> 01:15:42,687
SHE'S NOT EVEN HERE,
THANKS TO YOU.

1289
01:15:42,688 --> 01:15:45,807
WHAT THE HELL
ARE YOU DOING WITH HER?

1290
01:15:45,807 --> 01:15:48,309
WELL, DO YOU KNOW
WHERE SHE IS?

1291
01:15:48,310 --> 01:15:50,195
NO, I DON'T.

1292
01:15:50,195 --> 01:15:52,063
WHERE WAS SHE
SUPPOSED TO BE, ACCORDING TO YOU?

1293
01:15:52,064 --> 01:15:53,315
WE HAVE AN APPOINTMENT.

1294
01:15:53,315 --> 01:15:55,200
WHAT, AT THE CLINIC?

1295
01:15:55,817 --> 01:15:57,702
NO. AS A MATTER OF FACT,
I'M SUPPOSED TO MEET HER

1296
01:15:57,703 --> 01:15:59,571
ON THE ROAD
TO LOOKOUT MOUNTAIN.

1297
01:15:59,571 --> 01:16:01,456
IF SHE CALLS IN WILL YOU
TELL HER THAT, PLEASE?

1298
01:16:01,456 --> 01:16:03,324
I'M GONNA BACK UP THERE
AND WAIT FOR HER.

1299
01:16:03,325 --> 01:16:04,576
NO!

1300
01:16:04,576 --> 01:16:07,712
DON'T GO NEAR HER,
YOU SON OF A BITCH,

1301
01:16:07,713 --> 01:16:10,215
OR I SWEAR TO GOD,
I WILL KILL YOU.

1302
01:16:24,479 --> 01:16:25,730
Mark: YOU'RE GETTING
A LITTLE CLOSE TO THE EDGE,

1303
01:16:26,348 --> 01:16:28,233
SO COME OVER HERE AND
SIT ON THE RAILING.

1304
01:16:28,233 --> 01:16:30,735
Rachel: I AM NOT FALLING!
I'M FINE!

1305
01:16:30,736 --> 01:16:32,604
Echo: I'M FINE!
I'M FINE! I'M FINE!

1306
01:16:32,604 --> 01:16:35,106
OH, I FEEL
LIKE I'M FLYING!

1307
01:16:35,741 --> 01:16:36,358
AAH!

1308
01:16:38,860 --> 01:16:40,111
RACHEL!

1309
01:16:41,363 --> 01:16:43,248
PLEASE DON'T LET ME FALL.

1310
01:16:43,248 --> 01:16:44,499
RACHEL, I'VE GOT YOU.

1311
01:16:48,253 --> 01:16:52,624
AAH!

1312
01:17:16,398 --> 01:17:18,900
CARLA, COME AWAY
FROM THE EDGE.

1313
01:17:18,900 --> 01:17:20,785
DON'T COME ANY CLOSER.

1314
01:17:20,786 --> 01:17:22,654
CARLA,
YOU'VE ALREADY DONE IT.

1315
01:17:22,654 --> 01:17:25,790
YOU'RE CLOSE ENOUGH.
YOU'VE WON.

1316
01:17:25,791 --> 01:17:28,293
NO, THERE'S
NO WINNING FOR ME.

1317
01:17:30,796 --> 01:17:32,664
MAYBE YOU SHOULD
COME WITH ME

1318
01:17:32,664 --> 01:17:34,549
FOR ALL THE PEOPLE
YOU FAILED ON THE MOUNTAIN.

1319
01:17:34,549 --> 01:17:37,051
WHAT ARE YOU
TALKING ABOUT, CARLA?

1320
01:17:40,172 --> 01:17:41,423
MOUNT RAINIER.

1321
01:17:46,428 --> 01:17:49,564
LOOK, WE WERE ON A RIDGE
300 FEET FROM THE SUMMIT.

1322
01:17:49,564 --> 01:17:52,683
WE WERE FOLLOWING
AN ESTABLISHED ROUTE.

1323
01:17:52,684 --> 01:17:55,820
THERE'S A BIG CORNICE
OF SNOW AND ICE.

1324
01:17:55,821 --> 01:17:57,689
IT GAVE ALL SIGNS
OF BEING STABLE.

1325
01:17:57,689 --> 01:17:59,574
I WENT FIRST.
I CHECKED FOR CRACKS.

1326
01:17:59,574 --> 01:18:00,825
HOW'D YOU DO IT, THEN?

1327
01:18:01,443 --> 01:18:02,076
D'YOU CUT THE ROPE?

1328
01:18:02,694 --> 01:18:03,327
WHAT?
PUSH 'EM?

1329
01:18:03,945 --> 01:18:07,081
NO! IT WAS NOTHING
LIKE THAT AT ALL!

1330
01:18:07,082 --> 01:18:09,584
THEN HOW DID THEY DIE?

1331
01:18:13,338 --> 01:18:15,840
WHEN I STARTED BACK,

1332
01:18:15,841 --> 01:18:18,960
THE ICE PACK
STARTED TO FAIL.

1333
01:18:18,960 --> 01:18:22,713
THE SECTION
THEY WERE STANDING ON BROKE LOOSE.

1334
01:18:22,714 --> 01:18:23,965
I LOOKED DOWN.

1335
01:18:28,353 --> 01:18:30,221
IT HAPPENED SLOWLY.

1336
01:18:30,222 --> 01:18:32,107
I THINK I COULD'VE
SAVED THEM.

1337
01:18:32,107 --> 01:18:36,478
I KNOW I COULD HAVE.
I HAVE THE TRAINING, BUT...

1338
01:18:36,478 --> 01:18:38,980
BUT WHEN I LOOKED DOWN,

1339
01:18:38,980 --> 01:18:40,231
I COULDN'T MOVE.

1340
01:18:42,718 --> 01:18:45,821
I COULDN'T EVEN BREATHE.

1341
01:18:49,541 --> 01:18:50,792
I KNOW.

1342
01:18:52,627 --> 01:18:56,330
I KNOW WHAT THAT KIND
OF FEAR FEELS LIKE.

1343
01:19:02,504 --> 01:19:04,389
WERE THEY YOUR FRIENDS?

1344
01:19:04,389 --> 01:19:06,224
THEY WERE CLIENTS.

1345
01:19:06,224 --> 01:19:08,092
ALL EXCEPT FOR ONE.

1346
01:19:09,928 --> 01:19:13,064
WE WERE ENGAGED
TO BE MARRIED A MONTH LATER.

1347
01:19:31,116 --> 01:19:34,235
HOW DID YOU DO IT?

1348
01:19:34,236 --> 01:19:36,538
HOW DID YOU
GET OVER IT,

1349
01:19:36,538 --> 01:19:38,373
THE FEAR, THE GUILT?

1350
01:19:38,373 --> 01:19:39,624
I DIDN'T.

1351
01:19:39,624 --> 01:19:42,710
WHEN I'M ALONE
IN A HIGH PLACE,

1352
01:19:42,711 --> 01:19:45,213
I'M AS DIZZY AND
FRIGHTENED AS YOU ARE.

1353
01:19:46,465 --> 01:19:48,967
BUT WHEN I'M TEACHING
OTHER PEOPLE NOT TO BE AFRAID,

1354
01:19:48,967 --> 01:19:52,020
I'M NOT AFRAID.

1355
01:19:56,975 --> 01:19:58,860
IT'S OK.

1356
01:19:58,860 --> 01:20:00,111
COME ON.

1357
01:20:00,111 --> 01:20:01,362
COME ON.

1358
01:20:34,513 --> 01:20:37,015
MARK!
I TOLD YOU TO STAY AWAY FROM MY WIFE.

1359
01:20:37,015 --> 01:20:38,900
MARK, YOU DON'T
UNDERSTAND.

1360
01:20:38,900 --> 01:20:40,151
WAIT, WAIT.
WAIT A SECOND.

1361
01:20:40,151 --> 01:20:42,019
I THINK THERE'S BEEN
A MISUNDERSTANDING HERE.

1362
01:20:43,905 --> 01:20:45,773
Carla: STOP IT, ALL RIGHT?!
MARK, JUST LISTEN TO ME!

1363
01:20:46,408 --> 01:20:47,659
HEY, BACK UP NOW.

1364
01:20:47,659 --> 01:20:49,527
HOW DOES IT FEEL, DOCTOR,

1365
01:20:49,528 --> 01:20:52,664
TO BE ON THE BRINK YOURSELF,
THIS TIME, HUH?

1366
01:20:52,664 --> 01:20:53,915
Carla: MARK, STOP IT!

1367
01:20:53,915 --> 01:20:55,166
STOP IT. LOOK, YOU'RE
GONNA HAVE TO CALM--

1368
01:20:55,166 --> 01:20:56,417
STOP IT, ALL RIGHT?

1369
01:20:56,418 --> 01:20:57,669
CARLA, STAY BACK.

1370
01:20:58,920 --> 01:21:00,788
MARK! MARK!

1371
01:21:00,789 --> 01:21:01,422
MARK, STOP IT!

1372
01:21:05,176 --> 01:21:05,793
MARK!

1373
01:21:15,186 --> 01:21:17,054
HOLD ON, OK? HOLD ON!

1374
01:21:17,055 --> 01:21:20,191
MARK, THERE'S A ROPE
IN THE VAN. GET IT.

1375
01:21:27,065 --> 01:21:28,950
UH...

1376
01:21:28,950 --> 01:21:30,818
I DON'T THINK SO.

1377
01:21:30,819 --> 01:21:33,955
LOOK, WHAT HAPPENED
ON MOUNT RAINIER WAS AN ACCIDENT.

1378
01:21:33,955 --> 01:21:35,823
ALL RIGHT?
JUST GET THE ROPE!

1379
01:21:35,824 --> 01:21:39,577
IT'LL BE A MINUTE.
JUST HOLD ON.

1380
01:21:39,578 --> 01:21:41,463
NONE OF THAT MATTERS,
CARLA.

1381
01:21:41,463 --> 01:21:43,965
YOU KNOW...

1382
01:21:43,965 --> 01:21:47,718
YOU COULD'VE MADE THIS
A WHOLE LOT EASIER...

1383
01:21:47,719 --> 01:21:50,838
IF YOU'D HAVE JUST
DONE WHAT I SAID IN THE FIRST PLACE.

1384
01:21:50,839 --> 01:21:52,724
WHAT IS WRONG WITH YOU?

1385
01:21:52,724 --> 01:21:55,843
YOU DON'T GET IT,
DO YOU?

1386
01:21:55,844 --> 01:21:58,980
I TOLD <i>YOU</i> TO SIT
ON THE RAILING.

1387
01:22:01,483 --> 01:22:05,236
I RIGGED IT TO BREAK
FOR YOU, NOT RACHEL.

1388
01:22:15,246 --> 01:22:17,114
YOU KILLED RACHEL.

1389
01:22:17,115 --> 01:22:18,366
NO.

1390
01:22:18,366 --> 01:22:19,617
<i>YOU</i> DID.

1391
01:22:19,618 --> 01:22:21,503
YOU'RE THE ONE WHO DIDN'T
SIT ON THE RAILING

1392
01:22:21,503 --> 01:22:22,754
LIKE I TOLD YOU TO!

1393
01:22:22,754 --> 01:22:25,873
YOU WANTED ME TO FALL?

1394
01:22:27,125 --> 01:22:29,010
WHY?

1395
01:22:29,010 --> 01:22:30,261
AAH!

1396
01:22:32,130 --> 01:22:33,381
WHEN I MET YOU,

1397
01:22:33,381 --> 01:22:37,134
I DIDN'T HAVE 2 NICKELS
TO RUB TOGETHER.

1398
01:22:37,135 --> 01:22:40,888
YOU HAD YOUR PARENTS' MONEY
AND THAT BIG OLD HOUSE.

1399
01:22:42,774 --> 01:22:45,276
AND I COULD'VE HAD
ALL THAT.

1400
01:22:45,276 --> 01:22:47,144
EVEN RACHEL IF I WANTED.

1401
01:22:48,396 --> 01:22:50,898
SHE WAS SO MUCH MORE
CONTROLLABLE.

1402
01:22:50,899 --> 01:22:51,532
YOU...

1403
01:22:51,533 --> 01:22:53,401
YOU'RE STUBBORN.

1404
01:22:53,401 --> 01:22:56,537
YOU MAKE EVERYTHING
A MESS.

1405
01:22:56,538 --> 01:23:00,291
THAT'S WHY WHEN
THE DOCTOR CAME ALONG,

1406
01:23:00,291 --> 01:23:04,044
I FIGURED, "HEY,
HOW MUCH MORE PERFECT COULD THIS BE?"

1407
01:23:04,045 --> 01:23:07,164
A GUY WHO LIKES TO PUT
PEOPLE ON CLIFFS

1408
01:23:07,165 --> 01:23:09,667
AND SEE
IF THEY'LL JUMP?

1409
01:23:09,668 --> 01:23:11,553
THAT'S BEAUTIFUL.

1410
01:23:13,421 --> 01:23:15,923
FROM THEN ON,

1411
01:23:15,924 --> 01:23:19,677
I HAVE TO SAY IT WAS
ACTUALLY KIND OF FUN.

1412
01:23:19,678 --> 01:23:23,431
I KNEW YOU WERE TERRIFIED
OF COMING DOWN WITH YOUR MOTHER'S MENTAL ILLNESS,

1413
01:23:23,431 --> 01:23:25,933
SO I JUST
HELPED YOU ALONG A LITTLE BIT

1414
01:23:25,934 --> 01:23:27,819
BY DOSING YOU
